<i>♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah
Yeah, yeah, yeah... ♪</i>

16
00:01:05,106 --> 00:01:07,817
<i>I'm seeking my Indian Prince Charming...</i>

17
00:01:08,568 --> 00:01:12,864
...with a professional job and MBA.

18
00:01:13,990 --> 00:01:16,659
<i>At heart, I'm just a simple girl</i>

19
00:01:17,160 --> 00:01:19,496
<i>who loves weddings.</i>

20
00:01:19,579 --> 00:01:22,499
<i>♪ Do it in the pictures
Show me love ♪</i>

21
00:01:22,582 --> 00:01:24,250
<i>♪ And what's it gonna be ♪</i>

22
00:01:24,334 --> 00:01:28,505
<i>And I dream of having
a grand one of my own someday.</i>

23
00:01:28,588 --> 00:01:30,590
<i>♪ Show me love ♪</i>

24
00:01:30,673 --> 00:01:32,233
<i>♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah
Yeah, yeah, yeah... ♪</i>

25
00:01:32,801 --> 00:01:33,801
Don't do it.

26
00:01:34,177 --> 00:01:35,970
<i>♪ Show me love ♪</i>

27
00:01:36,054 --> 00:01:38,640
<i>♪ Oh, oh, show me love ♪</i>

28
00:01:44,604 --> 00:01:46,898
- [man] Look alive. Meeting's in 20.
- Huh?

29
00:01:49,317 --> 00:01:52,153
“Singapore equals economic miracle.”

30
00:01:52,737 --> 00:01:53,571
Brilliant.

31
00:01:53,655 --> 00:01:55,198
Please tell me you've slept.

32
00:01:55,281 --> 00:01:59,119
Oh. Yeah, I slept. I slept for 56 minutes.

33
00:01:59,202 --> 00:02:02,539
Asha, stop killing yourself.
This is what you've been waiting for.

34
00:02:02,622 --> 00:02:03,540
It's all on you.

35
00:02:03,623 --> 00:02:05,959
Now, get it together
and prove to my boss in London

36
00:02:06,042 --> 00:02:08,419
that I'm a genius
for stealing you from Wall St.

37
00:02:08,503 --> 00:02:09,671
Yes.

38
00:02:09,754 --> 00:02:11,548
- [woman] They're early!
- [tapping on glass]

39
00:02:11,631 --> 00:02:14,467
They just entered the building.
That's what you're wearing?

40
00:02:14,551 --> 00:02:17,303
I had a family thing last night.
Black or navy?

41
00:02:17,929 --> 00:02:19,848
- Black, definitely black.
- Mm-hmm.

42
00:02:19,931 --> 00:02:21,641
- Or maybe the navy?
- Tina!

43
00:02:21,724 --> 00:02:22,767
[man sighs]

44
00:02:22,851 --> 00:02:24,144
Some privacy, please?

45
00:02:28,439 --> 00:02:31,359
Singapore is a place
where economic miracles happen.

46
00:02:31,442 --> 00:02:35,405
And today, you have the opportunity
to help spread that miracle.

47
00:02:36,072 --> 00:02:40,618
Your investment is key to establishing
our Southeast Asia loan initiative.

48
00:02:41,202 --> 00:02:43,997
Which would launch Singapore as a powder...

49
00:02:45,373 --> 00:02:46,749
...ful, powerful...

50
00:02:48,626 --> 00:02:49,626
Powder...

51
00:02:51,588 --> 00:02:52,672
Pow... Powerful...

52
00:02:52,755 --> 00:02:53,965
Is something wrong here?

53
00:02:54,048 --> 00:02:55,592
No, of course not.

54
00:02:55,675 --> 00:02:57,343
Uh, definitely not. Definitely not.

55
00:02:58,178 --> 00:02:59,178
Um...

56
00:03:00,263 --> 00:03:01,263
The...

57
00:03:01,723 --> 00:03:02,807
Uh...

58
00:03:02,891 --> 00:03:07,520
This is your chance
to establish Singapore as a center...

59
00:03:07,604 --> 00:03:09,063
[Mrs. Tan] Okay, let's get to it.

60
00:03:09,147 --> 00:03:12,692
Micro loans aren't a cure for poverty.
It's one piece of a puzzle.

61
00:03:12,775 --> 00:03:16,154
Why Asia and why now? What's the strategy?

62
00:03:16,237 --> 00:03:20,533
Oh, well, we have 140 million borrowers,
80% women, 65% rural.

63
00:03:20,617 --> 00:03:23,995
Our annual growth is 12%
with a projected portfolio yield of...

64
00:03:24,078 --> 00:03:26,539
- Your numbers are impressive.
- Thank you.

65
00:03:26,623 --> 00:03:28,875
But what's the heart of your story?

66
00:03:30,460 --> 00:03:31,460
[whispers] Heart?

67
00:03:34,589 --> 00:03:35,506
Uh...

68
00:03:35,590 --> 00:03:37,383
We believe that women

69
00:03:38,176 --> 00:03:43,056
are key to social change by creating
a more sustainable future...

70
00:03:43,139 --> 00:03:46,851
Ms. Maurya, we believe
in your fund's potential to do good.

71
00:03:47,727 --> 00:03:50,563
But right now,
we're just not seeing your vision.

72
00:03:51,356 --> 00:03:52,899
[Asha] I mean, the vision is...

73
00:03:53,900 --> 00:03:56,069
- It's clear in the next slide.
- It's okay, Asha.

74
00:03:57,320 --> 00:03:58,988
[Asha] If you could give me one more...

75
00:03:59,072 --> 00:04:00,448
[sighs]

76
00:04:01,366 --> 00:04:02,367
That went well.

77
00:04:03,701 --> 00:04:04,619
I think.

78
00:04:04,702 --> 00:04:07,330
I can't believe my mom sent a guy to work
today of all days.

79
00:04:07,413 --> 00:04:10,124
Don't blame Mommy.
We've all botched pitches like that.

80
00:04:10,208 --> 00:04:12,126
Shake it off, move on.

81
00:04:12,210 --> 00:04:14,963
I can see why you're upset.
This is all lies.

82
00:04:15,046 --> 00:04:18,341
You're not a natural in the kitchen.
You're certainly not a simple girl.

83
00:04:18,424 --> 00:04:19,634
Can you take that down?

84
00:04:19,717 --> 00:04:21,636
I can't
because she's changed the password.

85
00:04:21,719 --> 00:04:23,429
Oh my God, this is a nightmare.

86
00:04:25,139 --> 00:04:27,600
I think he's got
a kind of hot accountant vibe.

87
00:04:28,226 --> 00:04:30,520
Like he could do times tables in his head.

88
00:04:31,312 --> 00:04:34,232
- [sighs]
- Are we still going out for coffee or...

89
00:04:34,315 --> 00:04:35,817
Look, I'm sorry, um...

90
00:04:36,317 --> 00:04:39,320
But this is my mother's fault. So...

91
00:04:40,238 --> 00:04:42,156
Yeah. Mine too.

92
00:04:42,240 --> 00:04:43,700
- Handle him.
- Yep.

93
00:04:44,993 --> 00:04:45,993
[woman] Sir.

94
00:04:46,661 --> 00:04:47,661
Just...

95
00:04:48,413 --> 00:04:50,164
This is for you. Call me.

96
00:04:50,665 --> 00:04:52,959
Please tell me
you can get me another shot.

97
00:04:53,543 --> 00:04:54,543
I'll try.

98
00:04:54,877 --> 00:04:57,463
And if I succeed, you'll have to show them

99
00:04:57,547 --> 00:05:00,633
why Asha Maurya cares
about this so damn much.

100
00:05:00,717 --> 00:05:03,052
We're not bankers. We're beggars.

101
00:05:03,136 --> 00:05:07,348
If we can't tell a good story,
our little tin cups remain empty.

102
00:05:07,432 --> 00:05:08,432
[crockery clinking]

103
00:05:08,474 --> 00:05:09,809
You ruined my pitch.

104
00:05:09,892 --> 00:05:12,562
Give me a heart attack
while you die alone in a gutter?

105
00:05:12,645 --> 00:05:15,940
Mom, you can't send a DesiDream date
to somebody's place of employment.

106
00:05:16,024 --> 00:05:19,402
Employment? This job doesn't pay
Asha enough to buy a condo.

107
00:05:19,485 --> 00:05:21,863
- Condos are a sound investment.
- I don't want one.

108
00:05:21,946 --> 00:05:24,907
You should've never left banking.
Your whole future was secure!

109
00:05:24,991 --> 00:05:27,035
- I got it.
- Oh, here we go again.

110
00:05:27,118 --> 00:05:30,997
Suneeta, don't make enemies
with a crocodile that shares your waters.

111
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:34,208
You know, that is so true, Mr. M.
About crocodiles.

112
00:05:34,792 --> 00:05:37,128
You're an economist, Vijay,
not a greeting card writer.

113
00:05:37,211 --> 00:05:40,089
I'm just sharing wisdom of their <i>dada-ji.</i>

114
00:05:40,173 --> 00:05:42,008
Nick, that's Priya's grandfather.

115
00:05:42,675 --> 00:05:44,302
Did she tell you about his boat?

116
00:05:44,385 --> 00:05:46,054
- Please, Dad. No.
- Boat? No.

117
00:05:46,137 --> 00:05:47,847
- [Nick] I love boats.
- So boring.

118
00:05:48,473 --> 00:05:49,599
Okay, Mom?

119
00:05:50,516 --> 00:05:54,395
All I'm asking is that you take down
this biodata and stop arranging dates.

120
00:05:54,479 --> 00:05:56,939
- Sorry, bio what?
- Biodata.

121
00:05:57,023 --> 00:06:00,943
Like a resume, except your mom writes it.
Instead of getting a job, you get married.

122
00:06:01,027 --> 00:06:06,240
No, no, no, no. This is not biodata.
This is a modern online profile.

123
00:06:06,324 --> 00:06:09,535
A nice way to meet a nice boy like this.

124
00:06:09,619 --> 00:06:12,538
- Meet Ravishanka Shah.
- Suneeta.

125
00:06:12,622 --> 00:06:15,166
Youngest Indian to win
the National Spelling Bee.

126
00:06:15,249 --> 00:06:17,794
- Mom.
- Went to MIT at 16.

127
00:06:17,877 --> 00:06:18,753
- Mom.
- Look, look!

128
00:06:18,836 --> 00:06:22,757
"Hello, I'm a very good boy.
I studied at MIT. I run a successful..."

129
00:06:22,840 --> 00:06:23,840
Mom!

130
00:06:25,885 --> 00:06:29,555
This poor boy's ma wrote this.
He has no idea it exists.

131
00:06:29,639 --> 00:06:30,640
[Vijay] Suneeta.

132
00:06:31,391 --> 00:06:34,602
Enjoy your feast.
This arguing is chewing my brains.

133
00:06:34,685 --> 00:06:38,606
Enjoy. This plate is for the husband
who should be here.

134
00:06:39,273 --> 00:06:40,274
[crockery clinking]

135
00:06:41,401 --> 00:06:44,320
I told her not to do this.
Don't get mad at me.

136
00:06:44,404 --> 00:06:48,574
Well, I will be calling you Mom
soon enough.

137
00:06:51,285 --> 00:06:52,203
[Suneeta clears throat]

138
00:06:52,286 --> 00:06:54,705
Oh, this biryani looks so good.

139
00:06:54,789 --> 00:06:55,665
It's just rice.

140
00:06:55,748 --> 00:06:57,583
And we don't really roll our Rs.

141
00:06:57,667 --> 00:07:00,044
- [sighs]
- Careful, it's spicy.

142
00:07:01,003 --> 00:07:02,880
- I love sp... [coughs]
- Oh!

143
00:07:03,548 --> 00:07:04,465
[Priya] You okay, babe?

144
00:07:04,549 --> 00:07:06,551
Mom, I'm not gonna meet this Ravi guy.

145
00:07:07,135 --> 00:07:08,177
Fine.

146
00:07:08,261 --> 00:07:09,429
Make me a liar.

147
00:07:10,096 --> 00:07:12,723
My God. You already told his mom
I'm gonna meet him, didn't you?

148
00:07:12,807 --> 00:07:15,977
Beta, I can't let you give up
just because of that <i>bekaar</i> Krish.

149
00:07:16,060 --> 00:07:19,313
Krish? This isn't about Krish.
Why does everyone think it is? It's not!

150
00:07:19,397 --> 00:07:22,608
- Calm down.
- I am over it. Why can't you be? God!

151
00:07:24,444 --> 00:07:25,444
[Suneeta exclaims]

152
00:07:25,903 --> 00:07:26,904
[sighs]

153
00:07:26,988 --> 00:07:28,739
Why would you mention Krish?

154
00:07:28,823 --> 00:07:30,783
Well, what am I supposed to do?

155
00:07:31,367 --> 00:07:35,204
[exhales] Just keep calm and curry on.

156
00:07:35,288 --> 00:07:37,748
- No, stop.
- I don't know why I said that.

157
00:07:44,422 --> 00:07:46,883
[Priya] Hey. You okay, sis?

158
00:07:46,966 --> 00:07:47,966
Yeah.

159
00:07:49,552 --> 00:07:51,429
[Priya] Okay, I need you to do me a favor.

160
00:07:52,430 --> 00:07:56,476
You and Mom can't go on like this.
I have too much on my plate.

161
00:07:56,559 --> 00:07:59,270
And I don't want Mom to be miserable
at my wedding.

162
00:07:59,353 --> 00:08:01,731
So you want me to be miserable instead?

163
00:08:01,814 --> 00:08:03,065
It's one date.

164
00:08:03,149 --> 00:08:04,400
It's a lie, Pri.

165
00:08:04,484 --> 00:08:07,320
- You lied about other boyfriends.
- Shh.

166
00:08:07,987 --> 00:08:11,157
- [whispers] Not in front of them.
- [Priya] You mean Ganesh and his gods?

167
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:13,201
- [Asha] Yeah.
- They already know.

168
00:08:13,284 --> 00:08:16,037
Come on, I was 16.
There was nothing to tell.

169
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:19,332
Honestly, I don't think
Mom and Dad want to know the truth.

170
00:08:19,415 --> 00:08:22,627
The fact we used to sneak out
to watch R-rated films?

171
00:08:22,710 --> 00:08:25,505
Or the fact that
you and Nick freaking live together?

172
00:08:25,588 --> 00:08:26,422
Shh.

173
00:08:26,506 --> 00:08:27,506
[Asha chuckles]

174
00:08:27,965 --> 00:08:30,092
Can you please help me out here?

175
00:08:30,176 --> 00:08:32,178
Be a maverick in three months.

176
00:08:33,095 --> 00:08:35,932
In the meantime,
if you want to be left alone,

177
00:08:36,015 --> 00:08:37,308
go on the date.

178
00:08:38,684 --> 00:08:40,686
[crockery clattering]

179
00:08:41,187 --> 00:08:43,856
Okay, fine.
I'll meet your little MIT genius.

180
00:08:43,940 --> 00:08:46,984
But no more setups
and you have to take down that profile.

181
00:08:47,068 --> 00:08:50,071
Okay, okay, as long as you agree
to go to the weddings also.

182
00:08:50,154 --> 00:08:52,615
- What?
- It's the best place to find a husband.

183
00:08:52,698 --> 00:08:53,824
I thought online was.

184
00:08:54,408 --> 00:08:55,576
That's also best.

185
00:08:55,660 --> 00:08:57,161
Mom, I have a life.

186
00:08:57,245 --> 00:08:58,663
This is your life too.

187
00:08:59,830 --> 00:09:01,040
You see this one?

188
00:09:01,123 --> 00:09:04,544
Sona's father picked us up from
the airport when we moved to this country.

189
00:09:04,627 --> 00:09:07,922
We had nothing. Eight dollars
and the clothes on our backs.

190
00:09:08,005 --> 00:09:10,049
Really? What was in your suitcases?

191
00:09:10,132 --> 00:09:11,884
The clothes that weren't on our backs.

192
00:09:12,426 --> 00:09:13,886
And this one.

193
00:09:13,970 --> 00:09:16,806
Rohit's mom took care of you
when Priya was born.

194
00:09:16,889 --> 00:09:18,307
That was Kumail's mom.

195
00:09:18,391 --> 00:09:23,187
No. I remember Kumail's mom was having
her gallbladder out. It was Rohit's mom.

196
00:09:23,271 --> 00:09:25,982
Okay, guys,
I... I know that these are your friends...

197
00:09:26,065 --> 00:09:29,569
Not friends, Asha. Family. Community.

198
00:09:29,652 --> 00:09:34,198
To you these are just weddings, but to us
this is a celebration of a life we built.

199
00:09:34,282 --> 00:09:35,449
From eight dollars.

200
00:09:35,533 --> 00:09:39,412
Do you understand that I may not want
a husband or partner in my life?

201
00:09:39,495 --> 00:09:41,664
Oh! No! [sobbing]

202
00:09:42,248 --> 00:09:43,874
- No!
- Suneeta?

203
00:09:43,958 --> 00:09:48,212
Oh, <i>beta.</i> I can't let you give up
on a lifetime of happiness.

204
00:09:48,296 --> 00:09:50,881
<i>Beta,</i> we just want what's best for you.

205
00:09:50,965 --> 00:09:52,216
[sobbing continues]

206
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:53,593
I know what you're doing.

207
00:09:53,676 --> 00:09:54,802
You always do this.

208
00:09:55,928 --> 00:09:57,597
Fine. I'll go to some weddings.

209
00:09:57,680 --> 00:10:01,434
- Not some. All. Show we're not ashamed.
- Mom.

210
00:10:01,517 --> 00:10:04,312
Look, if you do this,
I'll take down your profile.

211
00:10:04,395 --> 00:10:06,522
- Great.
- But you still have to meet Ravi.

212
00:10:06,606 --> 00:10:08,190
I have a good feeling about him.

213
00:10:08,274 --> 00:10:09,108
- No.
- Please.

214
00:10:09,191 --> 00:10:10,318
- Mom, no!
- Yes.

215
00:10:10,401 --> 00:10:11,611
- Mom! No!
<i>- Chup!</i>

216
00:10:12,403 --> 00:10:13,613
[waiter] Order up.

217
00:10:15,406 --> 00:10:17,325
[bell rings]

218
00:10:18,034 --> 00:10:19,285
[sensual music playing]

219
00:10:27,710 --> 00:10:29,754
[music builds to climax]

220
00:10:32,256 --> 00:10:33,758
[chuckles] Ravishankar Shah?

221
00:10:34,342 --> 00:10:36,427
- Oh. Hi! Um, just...
- Ravi?

222
00:10:36,510 --> 00:10:37,845
Just Ravi.

223
00:10:37,928 --> 00:10:42,683
- Do you mind if we order? I'm starving.
- Sure. Um, nice to meet you.

224
00:10:44,101 --> 00:10:44,977
What'll it be?

225
00:10:45,061 --> 00:10:50,483
Hi. Let me get a double-cheddar burger,
sloppy fries, large, and a water. Thanks.

226
00:10:51,150 --> 00:10:56,030
And he'll have a... What do you have
for “strict vegetarian seeks simple girl"?

227
00:10:56,113 --> 00:10:57,406
Uh...

228
00:10:57,490 --> 00:10:59,283
Not strict, not vegetarian.

229
00:10:59,367 --> 00:11:02,244
I'll have the same.
Just Coke, not water. Thank you.

230
00:11:02,328 --> 00:11:03,847
- [register keys chime]
- That'll be...

231
00:11:03,871 --> 00:11:06,540
Including 6.625 percent tax, 21.40.

232
00:11:08,042 --> 00:11:09,042
Nice.

233
00:11:09,669 --> 00:11:11,003
How'd you do that?

234
00:11:11,087 --> 00:11:13,506
Oh, just a simple girl thing. [chuckles]

235
00:11:14,215 --> 00:11:15,424
[inhales] Thanks.

236
00:11:15,925 --> 00:11:17,468
- Shall we?
- Mm-hmm.

237
00:11:23,140 --> 00:11:26,769
So, Ravi, can you really spell anything?

238
00:11:27,561 --> 00:11:28,561
Hmm.

239
00:11:30,523 --> 00:11:32,817
A-N-Y-T-H...

240
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:34,985
- Come on. Very funny.
- [chuckles]

241
00:11:35,069 --> 00:11:36,696
Spell "logorrhea."

242
00:11:36,779 --> 00:11:38,989
Listen, I don't dance on command. So...

243
00:11:39,073 --> 00:11:41,701
- Make your mom a liar? Spell "logorrhea."
- Seriously?

244
00:11:41,784 --> 00:11:42,660
Mm-hmm.

245
00:11:42,743 --> 00:11:46,914
Oh my God. Okay. Logorrhea.
L-O-G-O-R-R-H-E-A. Logorrhea.

246
00:11:47,707 --> 00:11:48,708
Well done.

247
00:11:48,791 --> 00:11:49,875
- Thank you.
- Definition?

248
00:11:49,959 --> 00:11:52,169
Verbal diarrhea.
Actually a good word for you.

249
00:11:52,253 --> 00:11:53,253
Ah.

250
00:11:54,380 --> 00:11:55,423
Bon appétit.

251
00:11:55,506 --> 00:12:00,010
Your mom forgot to mention your wit.
So subtle and sophisticated.

252
00:12:00,094 --> 00:12:04,306
- Yeah, yours left out a couple things too.
- Okay, fine. Here it goes.

253
00:12:04,390 --> 00:12:08,310
Uh, I blew up my engagement
to Jersey's most eligible brown bachelor,

254
00:12:08,394 --> 00:12:12,022
alienated my closest friends,
brought shame and calumny on my family.

255
00:12:12,106 --> 00:12:14,817
I'm no longer allowed
on public transport in Woodbridge.

256
00:12:14,900 --> 00:12:16,736
But that was a misunderstanding.

257
00:12:16,819 --> 00:12:19,780
Yeah, I was just gonna say
you're prettier in person.

258
00:12:19,864 --> 00:12:21,157
Did your mom write that too?

259
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:22,992
No, that was actually all me.

260
00:12:25,536 --> 00:12:26,536
Ravi.

261
00:12:28,122 --> 00:12:29,122
Asha.

262
00:12:30,166 --> 00:12:32,793
Literally, the only reason I agreed
to meet you here

263
00:12:32,877 --> 00:12:35,629
was so my mom would stop
posting my profile online.

264
00:12:36,130 --> 00:12:37,381
So this...

265
00:12:37,882 --> 00:12:38,716
Us...

266
00:12:38,799 --> 00:12:40,092
...is never gonna happen.

267
00:12:40,176 --> 00:12:41,385
Never gonna happen.

268
00:12:42,762 --> 00:12:43,929
How can you be so sure?

269
00:12:45,097 --> 00:12:47,016
Because our parents set this up.

270
00:12:47,641 --> 00:12:48,641
So?

271
00:12:49,185 --> 00:12:50,019
So?

272
00:12:50,102 --> 00:12:51,395
[scoffs]

273
00:12:51,479 --> 00:12:55,232
Wow. Okay. Um, how about this?
I just started a new job.

274
00:12:55,316 --> 00:12:58,861
It's consuming my life. I have no time
for anything else, and I'm okay with that.

275
00:12:58,944 --> 00:13:02,156
I just took a break from my job,
which was consuming my life.

276
00:13:02,239 --> 00:13:04,992
I have all the time in the world,
and I'm okay with that.

277
00:13:06,202 --> 00:13:08,370
So you basically, like, don't have a job?

278
00:13:08,454 --> 00:13:09,705
[chuckles] Well, actually, I...

279
00:13:09,789 --> 00:13:12,041
What happened to being the start-up guy?

280
00:13:12,124 --> 00:13:14,710
I made money off a start-up,
but it's not who I am.

281
00:13:14,794 --> 00:13:16,420
I prefer to do what I love.

282
00:13:16,504 --> 00:13:18,506
Most can't afford to make that choice.

283
00:13:18,589 --> 00:13:22,092
See, that's interesting.
Can't afford to or are afraid to?

284
00:13:24,553 --> 00:13:25,805
See? We're doomed.

285
00:13:26,722 --> 00:13:28,265
[scoffs] Okay.

286
00:13:28,349 --> 00:13:30,100
Oh, cheer up. You dodged a bullet.

287
00:13:30,184 --> 00:13:31,060
[Ravi] Mm-hmm.

288
00:13:31,143 --> 00:13:32,603
Anyway, a girl must eat.

289
00:13:33,771 --> 00:13:34,771
Mm.

290
00:13:35,648 --> 00:13:36,649
I'm gonna go.

291
00:13:37,233 --> 00:13:39,485
- Okay.
- Yeah. But, um...

292
00:13:40,569 --> 00:13:43,197
Thank you. This has been interesting.

293
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:44,448
[Asha] Mm-hmm.

294
00:13:46,492 --> 00:13:48,410
- Thanks for the burger.
- Anytime.

295
00:13:48,494 --> 00:13:49,620
Bon appétit.

296
00:13:49,703 --> 00:13:50,703
Yeah.

297
00:13:59,213 --> 00:14:01,048
[Ravi] Whoo! Happy birthday, Pops.

298
00:14:01,131 --> 00:14:04,468
So, Mr. Senior Citizen, how does it feel?

299
00:14:04,552 --> 00:14:08,556
Who'd have thought I'd be father to a man
in his 30s who still acts like a child?

300
00:14:08,639 --> 00:14:10,933
[Veena] Not today, Dinesh. Ravi is here.

301
00:14:11,016 --> 00:14:12,268
I got you this gift.

302
00:14:12,935 --> 00:14:14,436
No, no, no. No presents.

303
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:17,398
I cannot enjoy my birthday
until my son finds a wife.

304
00:14:17,481 --> 00:14:19,775
He's trying. He went out with Asha.

305
00:14:19,859 --> 00:14:22,486
Ha! And realized
that women want men not boys?

306
00:14:22,570 --> 00:14:23,654
[sighs] Dinesh.

307
00:14:23,737 --> 00:14:26,156
Dad, you wrote
this misleading profile of me.

308
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:30,119
Saying, "Looking for a simple girl."
I don't want simple. Simple is boring.

309
00:14:30,202 --> 00:14:31,704
You can't be so choosy.

310
00:14:31,787 --> 00:14:34,164
- Dad, I'm proud of my life.
- Oh, good.

311
00:14:34,248 --> 00:14:38,127
Proud of no job, proud of never dating,
proud of that T-shirt.

312
00:14:38,210 --> 00:14:41,881
You were so brilliant, Ravi. Huh? MIT!

313
00:14:41,964 --> 00:14:43,883
Dinesh, what's past is past.

314
00:14:44,842 --> 00:14:48,053
But now is the time for you
to find a good girl.

315
00:14:48,137 --> 00:14:50,097
- Mom.
- Good, not boring.

316
00:14:50,180 --> 00:14:51,765
There's nothing wrong with boring.

317
00:14:51,849 --> 00:14:53,893
Please, <i>beta.</i> Just try.

318
00:14:55,185 --> 00:14:56,020
For me.

319
00:14:56,103 --> 00:14:57,730
Okay fine, Mom. I'll try.

320
00:14:58,606 --> 00:15:00,983
[rhythmic music playing]

321
00:15:05,654 --> 00:15:06,947
Look what I found.

322
00:15:07,031 --> 00:15:09,491
Files on your secret love affair
with a British royal?

323
00:15:09,575 --> 00:15:11,285
Those were destroyed.

324
00:15:11,368 --> 00:15:15,372
These are case studies of every microloan
our company has ever funded.

325
00:15:15,456 --> 00:15:19,752
Plus, a 1997 swimsuit edition
of <i>Foxy Gals</i> magazine.

326
00:15:19,835 --> 00:15:21,420
Now, I know this isn't yours.

327
00:15:21,503 --> 00:15:24,048
Don't be so sure. I did go to college.

328
00:15:24,673 --> 00:15:28,177
So folders. Like the 1800s?

329
00:15:28,260 --> 00:15:30,137
More like the last 25 years.

330
00:15:30,220 --> 00:15:33,515
I want you to analyze these
and learn what we do,

331
00:15:33,599 --> 00:15:35,643
how we do it, and why we do it.

332
00:15:35,726 --> 00:15:37,526
- [Asha] That could take all summer.
- Mm-hmm.

333
00:15:37,603 --> 00:15:40,439
I want you to be so brilliant,
Singapore can't say no.

334
00:15:40,522 --> 00:15:42,149
But they did say no.

335
00:15:42,232 --> 00:15:46,070
I spoke to the higher-ups in London
and a personal friend.

336
00:15:46,153 --> 00:15:49,365
They'll see if they can pull strings
to bring them back.

337
00:15:49,448 --> 00:15:51,700
- If you screw up this time...
- Heads will roll.

338
00:15:51,784 --> 00:15:53,202
[man] That's a bit medieval.

339
00:15:53,285 --> 00:15:55,287
But yes, your head and mine.

340
00:15:56,330 --> 00:16:00,209
I'll also probably lose my job.
I'll have to take my kid out of preschool.

341
00:16:00,292 --> 00:16:02,670
- There goes Princeton!
- Ambitious, this one.

342
00:16:02,753 --> 00:16:03,753
Come, come.

343
00:16:04,171 --> 00:16:07,299
- Mom, I'm at work.
- Oh, no. Don't "I'm at work" me.

344
00:16:07,383 --> 00:16:08,801
Now what did I do?

345
00:16:08,884 --> 00:16:11,136
- You behaved like a total fool!
- What?

346
00:16:11,220 --> 00:16:14,348
Pooja Patel told me
you gave Ravi Shah diarrhea!

347
00:16:14,431 --> 00:16:16,767
What? No! I asked him to spell logorrhea.

348
00:16:17,434 --> 00:16:19,728
- What's that?
- Verbal diarrhea.

349
00:16:19,812 --> 00:16:21,855
You mean diarrhea from the mo...

350
00:16:22,606 --> 00:16:27,403
Oh. Well, you better behave
at the next wedding or our deal is off!

351
00:16:27,486 --> 00:16:29,488
[soft emotional music playing]

352
00:16:30,155 --> 00:16:32,992
[Hindu priest] Today,
our bride and groom come together

353
00:16:33,075 --> 00:16:36,245
to celebrate both the Hindu
and Jewish traditions,

354
00:16:37,037 --> 00:16:39,373
to learn the best of what
each has to offer,

355
00:16:39,456 --> 00:16:42,876
confirming that love,
spoken of in all religions,

356
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:44,586
is our true meeting place.

357
00:16:45,504 --> 00:16:50,718
It is their promise to be honest, open,
loyal, and devoted to one another.

358
00:16:50,801 --> 00:16:55,347
This responsibility speaks of faith
and the love and support of your friends.

359
00:16:56,265 --> 00:16:58,100
[wedding guest] Mazel tov!

360
00:16:58,183 --> 00:16:59,226
[guests cheering]

361
00:16:59,309 --> 00:17:01,311
["Hava Nagila" playing]

362
00:17:14,241 --> 00:17:16,827
[all cheering]

363
00:17:18,954 --> 00:17:20,998
I lost Nick to the uncles.

364
00:17:21,081 --> 00:17:23,000
Better than the bridesmaids.

365
00:17:24,001 --> 00:17:26,545
Beats getting hit on
by that spelling bee nerd.

366
00:17:26,628 --> 00:17:29,757
"Hi, I'm Ravi. I went to MIT.
Wanna play Bananagrams with me?"

367
00:17:29,840 --> 00:17:32,676
"No, thanks, Mr. Nerd.
I'd rather clean a shower drain."

368
00:17:34,428 --> 00:17:36,013
Ah. [chuckles]

369
00:17:36,096 --> 00:17:37,222
- You're the nerd.
- Mm-hmm.

370
00:17:37,306 --> 00:17:39,600
Yeah. I'm a nerd.
I'm a nerd. I love nerds.

371
00:17:40,434 --> 00:17:42,269
SAT scores through the roof!

372
00:17:42,352 --> 00:17:43,479
Okay, I'm gonna go.

373
00:17:43,562 --> 00:17:45,564
- Good save, though. Smooth.
- Yeah. Yep.

374
00:17:46,982 --> 00:17:48,275
You look thirsty.

375
00:17:48,358 --> 00:17:49,985
Uh, I was actually just leaving.

376
00:17:50,069 --> 00:17:51,528
Oh, you're leaving this time?

377
00:17:52,071 --> 00:17:55,157
- Why tell Pooja Patel about our date?
- Pooja who?

378
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:58,368
Pooja Patel,
the gossip queen of Little India?

379
00:17:59,203 --> 00:18:01,789
I didn't tell anyone.
Why would I tell someone?

380
00:18:01,872 --> 00:18:04,124
Huh. She was spying on us.

381
00:18:04,750 --> 00:18:06,085
Unbelievable.

382
00:18:07,586 --> 00:18:09,213
Asha, darling.

383
00:18:09,713 --> 00:18:12,049
Ravi. Did you call my niece Twinkle?

384
00:18:12,132 --> 00:18:14,676
[Sheela Auntie] She's Miss India,
New Jersey, you know.

385
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:17,679
- Nah, Pinky Au...
- She's no brain like you, huh?

386
00:18:17,763 --> 00:18:20,891
But a spelling bee is no Nobel Prize.

387
00:18:21,809 --> 00:18:24,520
Pinky, leave Ravi.
Ravi has time. But Asha.

388
00:18:24,603 --> 00:18:27,314
Suneeta must be desperate.

389
00:18:27,397 --> 00:18:32,611
All these doctors and lawyers and PhDs,
they will be snapped up in no time.

390
00:18:32,694 --> 00:18:35,197
And you will be stuck with leftovers.

391
00:18:35,906 --> 00:18:39,868
Think of the shame! Krish getting married
to a younger woman so soon.

392
00:18:39,952 --> 00:18:45,040
- Oh my God. You didn't know.<i> Bechari.
- Bechari,</i> Asha, <i>beti. Arre.</i>

393
00:18:45,124 --> 00:18:46,500
You know, really, I'm fine.

394
00:18:46,583 --> 00:18:47,793
No. You know what?

395
00:18:47,876 --> 00:18:51,171
Best thing, you get your revenge
and get engaged quickly.

396
00:18:51,255 --> 00:18:53,340
Oh, I'm not looking for revenge.

397
00:18:53,423 --> 00:18:56,343
I'm looking for a bit of time
to focus on my career.

398
00:18:56,426 --> 00:18:59,721
Darling, careers fade away,
but a husband and a family?

399
00:18:59,805 --> 00:19:01,306
Those are forever, darling.

400
00:19:01,390 --> 00:19:03,350
They're handing out wedding favors
if you wanna...

401
00:19:03,433 --> 00:19:05,060
<i>Beta, </i>don't worry.

402
00:19:05,144 --> 00:19:09,565
We promise not to give up on you
until we know that you're happy.

403
00:19:10,732 --> 00:19:11,567
Happy.

404
00:19:11,650 --> 00:19:13,110
- A hundred percent.
- Yes.

405
00:19:13,694 --> 00:19:16,196
But... can't you see?

406
00:19:16,280 --> 00:19:17,865
I <i>am</i> happy.

407
00:19:17,948 --> 00:19:21,326
Thrilled, in fact,
'cause I met someone too.

408
00:19:22,369 --> 00:19:24,746
My Indian Prince Charming right here.

409
00:19:26,623 --> 00:19:27,708
You two?

410
00:19:27,791 --> 00:19:29,209
[giggles] No, no, no.

411
00:19:29,293 --> 00:19:31,879
I heard from Pooja Patel
it was a disaster.

412
00:19:31,962 --> 00:19:34,089
Disaster? Us? No.

413
00:19:34,173 --> 00:19:37,676
We are the opposite of disaster.
We are perfect together.

414
00:19:37,759 --> 00:19:39,887
Aren't we, Rav? Ravi?

415
00:19:39,970 --> 00:19:41,513
- Uh-huh.
- [Asha] Ravster.

416
00:19:41,597 --> 00:19:46,226
She's the simple girl I always wanted,
you know? Right, Asha? Shh.

417
00:19:46,310 --> 00:19:48,812
Very good.
Good luck to you and your simple girl.

418
00:19:48,896 --> 00:19:50,731
<i>Chalo,</i> Pinky. Let's go.

419
00:19:52,816 --> 00:19:53,816
We'll see.

420
00:19:55,027 --> 00:19:55,861
Seriously?

421
00:19:55,944 --> 00:19:58,530
- They're gone, aren't they?
- Yeah, to spread the news.

422
00:19:58,614 --> 00:20:01,408
Come on, I'll just tell them
we broke up at the next wedding.

423
00:20:01,491 --> 00:20:04,828
Then they'll just keep coming back.
So, yeah, good luck.

424
00:20:04,912 --> 00:20:08,207
- Wait. What if I didn't say that?
- Okay.

425
00:20:09,416 --> 00:20:12,377
Would it be so bad to let people think
we're off the market?

426
00:20:12,461 --> 00:20:13,901
Is this how you're gonna ask me out?

427
00:20:13,962 --> 00:20:16,840
I am not asking you out.
Not for real, anyway.

428
00:20:16,924 --> 00:20:19,927
- I dunno where you're going with this.
- You don't have to do anything!

429
00:20:20,010 --> 00:20:23,013
Just fend off the matchmaking aunties
so I can get some work done.

430
00:20:23,096 --> 00:20:25,766
Mm-hmm. Hmm. What's in it for me?

431
00:20:26,433 --> 00:20:27,768
You get your life back.

432
00:20:27,851 --> 00:20:29,228
I have my life.

433
00:20:31,897 --> 00:20:34,024
Uh, no, you don't.

434
00:20:35,025 --> 00:20:36,025
Come on.

435
00:20:38,153 --> 00:20:40,864
[Asha] Think about it. How many
Indian weddings are you invited to?

436
00:20:40,948 --> 00:20:42,157
- Sixteen.
- Nineteen.

437
00:20:42,241 --> 00:20:44,993
We go to the ones we're both invited to.
Brings it down to 14.

438
00:20:45,077 --> 00:20:47,847
- How'd you come up with that?
- Math whiz. Don't question the numbers.

439
00:20:47,871 --> 00:20:50,082
Well, Asha, I'm not even agreeing to one.

440
00:20:50,165 --> 00:20:53,043
If we join forces,
we won't have to deal with all of this.

441
00:20:53,126 --> 00:20:55,712
- Some people enjoy this.
- Do you, Ravi?

442
00:20:55,796 --> 00:20:57,965
You wanna lie, tell everyone we're dating.

443
00:20:58,048 --> 00:21:01,009
Not lie, just role-play
until wedding season's over.

444
00:21:01,093 --> 00:21:02,719
I'm offering you a choice.

445
00:21:02,803 --> 00:21:05,389
Summer with me or summer with...

446
00:21:05,472 --> 00:21:06,306
her.

447
00:21:06,390 --> 00:21:07,516
Hi, Pinky Auntie.

448
00:21:08,433 --> 00:21:10,477
Yeah, I'm gonna pass on both.

449
00:21:11,812 --> 00:21:14,314
Fine, I'll pay you. Fifty bucks a wedding.

450
00:21:14,398 --> 00:21:15,774
God. You're kidding me.

451
00:21:15,857 --> 00:21:17,317
- Seventy-five.
- No.

452
00:21:17,401 --> 00:21:19,111
- One hundred, final offer.
- Five hundred.

453
00:21:19,194 --> 00:21:21,321
- What?
- I'm kidding. [chuckles]

454
00:21:21,405 --> 00:21:25,033
Seriously, I'm not interested
in a pretend relationship, okay?

455
00:21:25,117 --> 00:21:26,368
Can we please focus?

456
00:21:26,451 --> 00:21:29,371
Don't be so selfish.
Do this for your parents.

457
00:21:29,454 --> 00:21:31,748
At least until wedding season is over.

458
00:21:32,916 --> 00:21:35,377
<i>He agreed to fake date you?
What's wrong with him?</i>

459
00:21:35,460 --> 00:21:36,753
<i>Actually, what's wrong with you?</i>

460
00:21:36,837 --> 00:21:39,089
I'm a genius, that's what's wrong with me.

461
00:21:39,172 --> 00:21:40,652
What you gonna do when mom finds out?

462
00:21:40,716 --> 00:21:43,218
She'll be thrilled.
That's the whole point.

463
00:21:43,302 --> 00:21:45,762
How do half a billion women
wear these things?

464
00:21:45,846 --> 00:21:48,890
Yeah, she'll be thrilled
until she finds out the truth.

465
00:21:48,974 --> 00:21:52,227
Relax. He's an MIT start-up founder.
He's every mom's dream.

466
00:21:53,562 --> 00:21:58,984
[sighs] And the best part is,
nobody has to be miserable anymore.

467
00:21:59,484 --> 00:22:01,445
[grunts, chokes]

468
00:22:02,946 --> 00:22:04,072
[pipe screeching]

469
00:22:04,573 --> 00:22:07,951
Dad, please just let me buy you
a new dishwasher?

470
00:22:08,035 --> 00:22:11,204
That is so typical
of your generation, huh?

471
00:22:11,288 --> 00:22:13,790
Throw money
every time there's a little problem.

472
00:22:14,291 --> 00:22:15,375
[sighs]

473
00:22:15,459 --> 00:22:19,087
You know, Dad, um, you'll be happy
to hear this, actually, um...

474
00:22:19,880 --> 00:22:21,798
- I'm gonna see Asha again.
- Oh really?

475
00:22:21,882 --> 00:22:23,050
- Yeah.
- Hmm.

476
00:22:23,133 --> 00:22:24,009
She agreed?

477
00:22:24,092 --> 00:22:25,844
Yeah, Dad, she agreed.

478
00:22:25,927 --> 00:22:27,637
To go out with you again?

479
00:22:27,721 --> 00:22:28,721
Yes.

480
00:22:30,015 --> 00:22:31,224
Are you sure?

481
00:22:31,308 --> 00:22:32,601
Yeah, Dad, I'm sure.

482
00:22:33,435 --> 00:22:34,895
<i>Bete, </i>listen to me.

