00:35:00,181 --> 00:35:02,391
- Desert me and you're fired.
- Okay.

724
00:35:02,475 --> 00:35:06,062
Now, come on.
Let's enjoy this bargain drink,

725
00:35:06,687 --> 00:35:11,400
this impossibly hip DJ,
and whatever it is hanging in this room.

726
00:35:13,569 --> 00:35:16,531
Hey, do you think
that DJ would do Priya's wedding?

727
00:35:17,031 --> 00:35:20,243
Maybe you should go check.
And look out for donors on the way.

728
00:35:20,952 --> 00:35:21,994
Copy that.

729
00:35:27,625 --> 00:35:28,625
Uh...

730
00:35:29,085 --> 00:35:30,085
Hi.

731
00:35:31,212 --> 00:35:32,255
Mr. DJ?

732
00:35:32,797 --> 00:35:37,385
Um, I'm sorry to interrupt your set,
and I don't want to cause offense.

733
00:35:37,468 --> 00:35:41,305
But is there any chance
that you do weddings at all?

734
00:35:42,056 --> 00:35:45,476
Uh, actually, someone's booked me solid
on the Indian wedding circuit.

735
00:35:45,560 --> 00:35:46,644
[Asha] Ravi?

736
00:35:49,188 --> 00:35:50,565
Sinus infection cleared up?

737
00:35:50,648 --> 00:35:52,608
Um, well, NyQuil.

738
00:35:53,776 --> 00:35:56,070
- So you're...
- Spellbound. Am I right?

739
00:35:56,154 --> 00:35:57,989
- Mm-hmm.
- [man chuckles]

740
00:35:58,072 --> 00:36:00,658
- Ravi, this is my boss...
- James?

741
00:36:01,450 --> 00:36:02,535
Yo.

742
00:36:03,161 --> 00:36:05,079
- [chuckles]
- Yes.

743
00:36:05,163 --> 00:36:08,416
You'd think they'd have nicer cheese
at a fancy gig like this.

744
00:36:08,499 --> 00:36:09,917
That's butter, dude.

745
00:36:10,585 --> 00:36:13,379
How do you both know each other?

746
00:36:13,462 --> 00:36:18,467
I heard him play a few sets at a club
in Ibiza back in my party boy days.

747
00:36:18,551 --> 00:36:19,927
He brought the house down.

748
00:36:20,011 --> 00:36:22,096
- [Ravi and James chuckle]
- Clearly.

749
00:36:22,805 --> 00:36:23,848
Okay.

750
00:36:23,931 --> 00:36:25,683
Well, I'm gonna go schmooze.

751
00:36:25,766 --> 00:36:27,185
- I'm gonna...
- Not you.

752
00:36:27,268 --> 00:36:28,436
Enjoy the butter.

753
00:36:28,519 --> 00:36:29,519
Thanks, buddy.

754
00:36:31,480 --> 00:36:33,024
You want to grab some air?

755
00:36:33,107 --> 00:36:35,568
Yeah, uh, I could do air.

756
00:36:35,651 --> 00:36:36,694
Air is good.

757
00:36:36,777 --> 00:36:39,071
Keep it chill. No lasers.

758
00:36:39,155 --> 00:36:41,157
- Have a little faith, Rav.
- I have no faith.

759
00:36:41,240 --> 00:36:42,366
Nice to see you, Yoshi.

760
00:36:42,450 --> 00:36:44,952
Nice to see you too.
Is your sister still engaged?

761
00:36:45,036 --> 00:36:46,245
[Asha] Yes, she is.

762
00:36:46,329 --> 00:36:47,705
[Yoshi] All right, cool.

763
00:36:48,414 --> 00:36:50,541
How's everyone doing? All right.

764
00:36:50,625 --> 00:36:53,794
DJ Spellbound's a little busy,
so Yoshi's in the house.

765
00:36:55,338 --> 00:36:58,883
- So, DJ Spellbound, huh?
- Mm-hmm.

766
00:36:58,966 --> 00:37:01,719
- That's not ironic at all.
- [chuckles]

767
00:37:02,220 --> 00:37:05,681
You know, it started as joke,
but, um, kinda just stuck.

768
00:37:05,765 --> 00:37:06,891
Hmm.

769
00:37:09,644 --> 00:37:10,811
[chuckles softly]

770
00:37:12,313 --> 00:37:17,568
So, um, what's your big secret?
Why don't you have a real boyfriend?

771
00:37:18,152 --> 00:37:19,737
- [Asha scoffs]
- [Ravi chuckles]

772
00:37:20,363 --> 00:37:22,531
Why don't I have a real boyfriend?

773
00:37:22,615 --> 00:37:24,575
I think it's a legit question here.

774
00:37:25,076 --> 00:37:26,577
Okay, yeah. It is.

775
00:37:27,453 --> 00:37:34,001
After things ended with Krish,
I figured why stop there?

776
00:37:34,585 --> 00:37:35,585
Mm.

777
00:37:36,170 --> 00:37:43,052
So I quit my job, moved to Jersey
in the hope of starting over in many ways.

778
00:37:43,719 --> 00:37:44,595
[sighs]

779
00:37:44,679 --> 00:37:47,974
Of course, my mom thinks
I quit banking just to spite her.

780
00:37:48,057 --> 00:37:49,475
- Did you?
- Probably.

781
00:37:49,558 --> 00:37:50,558
[chuckles]

782
00:37:52,061 --> 00:37:56,315
So what about you?
DJ... ing, how did that happen?

783
00:37:56,399 --> 00:38:00,236
You know, my backup skill set is spelling
incredibly esoteric words.

784
00:38:00,319 --> 00:38:02,029
Can't really make a living off that.

785
00:38:02,113 --> 00:38:03,906
- Logorrhea. I mean...
- Logorrhea.

786
00:38:05,032 --> 00:38:09,954
But no, like, when I was a kid,
everything I did was for my parents.

787
00:38:10,037 --> 00:38:14,292
Right? Everything. Except music.
Music was for me.

788
00:38:14,375 --> 00:38:16,544
I mean, music used to make me happy.

789
00:38:17,086 --> 00:38:20,256
But, uh, lately, I don't know. I mean...

790
00:38:21,674 --> 00:38:25,011
I've been on the road for, like,
ten years just working nonstop.

791
00:38:25,094 --> 00:38:27,179
I don't know what I'm working for anymore.

792
00:38:27,847 --> 00:38:28,847
So...

793
00:38:29,348 --> 00:38:34,186
I figured I'd take a break,
just come back home and fix my family.

794
00:38:34,270 --> 00:38:35,270
[scoffs]

795
00:38:35,688 --> 00:38:38,149
I'm sorry. It's kind of complicated.

796
00:38:46,449 --> 00:38:48,409
[high energy dance music playing]

797
00:38:48,492 --> 00:38:49,994
Damn it, Yoshi.

798
00:38:50,077 --> 00:38:52,663
- I'm sorry. I gotta...
- Yeah, you gotta go.

799
00:38:52,747 --> 00:38:54,790
- DJ stuff.
- Yeah, I gotta... Right.

800
00:38:55,708 --> 00:38:56,792
Are we good?

801
00:38:57,752 --> 00:39:01,464
We're good. We're cool. Yeah.

802
00:39:01,547 --> 00:39:02,547
Great.

803
00:39:03,466 --> 00:39:04,467
Yoshi!

804
00:39:06,093 --> 00:39:07,093
Oh, God.

805
00:39:09,472 --> 00:39:11,599
I can't believe he's Spellbound.

806
00:39:11,682 --> 00:39:14,310
[Asha] Wait, you actually know who he is?

807
00:39:14,393 --> 00:39:17,980
I don't, I'm a nerd,
but he's got like a gazillion followers.

808
00:39:18,064 --> 00:39:19,982
I do not trust DJs.

809
00:39:20,066 --> 00:39:21,835
- [Asha chuckles]
- Why? What's wrong with DJs?

810
00:39:21,859 --> 00:39:24,046
I'm sure they're talented.
I don't understand what they do,

811
00:39:24,070 --> 00:39:25,154
so don't respect it.

812
00:39:25,237 --> 00:39:27,698
- What's he hiding?
- I don't think he's hiding anything.

813
00:39:27,782 --> 00:39:28,949
It just never came up.

814
00:39:29,033 --> 00:39:34,288
You've been to a bazillion weddings
and never asked him about his background?

815
00:39:36,374 --> 00:39:38,626
I... I didn't want him
to get the wrong idea.

816
00:39:38,709 --> 00:39:41,545
Ash, what if it's not the wrong idea?

817
00:39:41,629 --> 00:39:43,798
Priya, have you been talking to Mom again?

818
00:39:43,881 --> 00:39:45,966
Let it happen. You want it, sis.

819
00:39:46,050 --> 00:39:46,926
- Shh!
- [Priya] But...

820
00:39:47,009 --> 00:39:48,969
What you want...

821
00:39:51,722 --> 00:39:53,849
is a Mumbai Monster.

822
00:39:53,933 --> 00:39:55,768
A Mumbai Monster.

823
00:39:56,268 --> 00:39:57,103
What is it?

824
00:39:57,186 --> 00:40:02,566
It's a masala mojito infused
with cumin seeds and Kashmiri chilies.

825
00:40:02,650 --> 00:40:03,651
It is...

826
00:40:04,860 --> 00:40:06,028
- [chokes]
- [Asha] Oh.

827
00:40:06,112 --> 00:40:07,363
That good, huh?

828
00:40:07,446 --> 00:40:08,989
Oh my God. That's disgusting.

829
00:40:09,073 --> 00:40:12,034
So what do we know about him?

830
00:40:12,618 --> 00:40:16,414
Okay, he was born in Jersey City
and he graduated MIT 2011.

831
00:40:16,497 --> 00:40:19,708
My pal Joby graduated in 2010.
I can see what I can find out.

832
00:40:19,792 --> 00:40:21,627
No, we're not snooping on Ravi.

833
00:40:21,710 --> 00:40:22,753
[Nick] It's not snooping.

834
00:40:22,837 --> 00:40:26,090
I'm collecting information
about him without him knowing.

835
00:40:26,173 --> 00:40:30,261
If he is gonna join our family,
we got to find out who he really is.

836
00:40:30,344 --> 00:40:33,264
He's not joining our family, guys, okay?
We're just...

837
00:40:33,347 --> 00:40:35,516
You're just more than fake dating.

838
00:40:35,599 --> 00:40:37,476
You like him, admit it.

839
00:40:39,603 --> 00:40:42,690
So Nick, how's the, um...
How's the Hindi coming along?

840
00:40:44,650 --> 00:40:48,279
[in Hindi] The bride is
driving pickles around.

841
00:40:51,115 --> 00:40:52,241
[in English] He's very good.

842
00:40:52,908 --> 00:40:54,076
[low chuckle]

843
00:40:55,077 --> 00:40:57,037
I said, "It's going great." Right?

844
00:40:57,121 --> 00:40:57,955
Pretty much.

845
00:40:58,038 --> 00:41:02,251
Hey, babe. Maybe you don't need
to try so hard to impress Mom and Dad.

846
00:41:02,334 --> 00:41:03,544
Yes, I do. I do.

847
00:41:04,295 --> 00:41:06,338
Nick, you're a neurosurgeon.

848
00:41:06,422 --> 00:41:07,423
Here's the thing.

849
00:41:07,506 --> 00:41:12,761
A binary craniotomy is nothing
compared to planning an Indian wedding.

850
00:41:12,845 --> 00:41:14,763
And I really want this to go well.

851
00:41:14,847 --> 00:41:17,224
My parents were barely married
seven years.

852
00:41:17,308 --> 00:41:23,898
In Indian traditions,
the souls are linked for seven lifetimes.

853
00:41:26,317 --> 00:41:28,986
Wow, that's a long time, babe.

854
00:41:29,570 --> 00:41:31,405
It's not nearly enough, pumpkin.

855
00:41:32,907 --> 00:41:33,907
Okay.

856
00:41:35,326 --> 00:41:36,827
[Asha] I am starving!

857
00:41:36,911 --> 00:41:40,039
[Ravi] Me too. Who runs out of food
at a wedding? Come on!

858
00:41:40,122 --> 00:41:42,875
[Asha] There wasn't even
a garlic naan in sight. Whoa!

859
00:41:44,084 --> 00:41:45,753
Holy crap, Ravi.

860
00:41:48,130 --> 00:41:49,882
You live here by yourself?

861
00:41:49,965 --> 00:41:54,261
When I'm not traveling, yeah.
I don't get to spend much time here, so...

862
00:41:54,345 --> 00:41:57,890
It's kind of nice, being at home.
Though I did have fun on the road.

863
00:41:57,973 --> 00:41:59,433
[Asha] Yeah, I can see that.

864
00:41:59,517 --> 00:42:02,186
Anyway, you didn't finish your story.
So you moved to Jersey...

865
00:42:02,269 --> 00:42:03,145
[Asha] Mm-hmm.

866
00:42:03,229 --> 00:42:04,230
Now what?

867
00:42:04,313 --> 00:42:07,316
- Now I change the world.
- [Ravi chuckles]

868
00:42:08,484 --> 00:42:13,656
No, but seriously, starting this fund up
has been way harder than I expected.

869
00:42:13,739 --> 00:42:16,659
Yeah. Well, you know,
anything worth doing is hard, right?

870
00:42:16,742 --> 00:42:19,578
I remember when I first started DJing

871
00:42:19,662 --> 00:42:22,456
my parents threatened
to stop paying for MIT. It was scary.

872
00:42:22,540 --> 00:42:23,958
So what did you do?

873
00:42:24,041 --> 00:42:26,085
I knew exactly what to do. I panicked.

874
00:42:26,168 --> 00:42:27,336
[both chuckle]

875
00:42:28,379 --> 00:42:30,214
Parents, happiness. Happiness, parents.

876
00:42:30,297 --> 00:42:33,342
Yeah. Here's to not letting them
drown that inner voice.

877
00:42:33,425 --> 00:42:34,635
[Asha] Hmm.

878
00:42:38,347 --> 00:42:40,891
Although, you know
what my inner voice is saying right now?

879
00:42:41,850 --> 00:42:42,851
What?

880
00:42:43,352 --> 00:42:44,770
<i>Yo quiero</i> Taco Bell.

881
00:42:44,853 --> 00:42:47,064
- Oh my God.
- I need Taco Bell.

882
00:42:47,147 --> 00:42:50,359
[chuckles] Okay,
every Indian loves Taco Bell.

883
00:42:50,442 --> 00:42:51,694
[Asha inhales]

884
00:42:51,777 --> 00:42:53,445
- [phone chimes]
- Give me a sec.

885
00:42:53,529 --> 00:42:55,823
- Where are the plates?
- Uh, second cabinet.

886
00:42:55,906 --> 00:42:56,906
[Asha] Okay.

887
00:42:58,742 --> 00:43:02,121
Yoshi. Um, Good Samaritan needs,
like, 27 number eights.

888
00:43:03,205 --> 00:43:07,418
Yeah. Patesh will meet you out back.
And don't forget the mango pickle.

889
00:43:08,210 --> 00:43:10,379
Yeah, and do not be seen again.

890
00:43:11,589 --> 00:43:12,589
All right.

891
00:43:14,174 --> 00:43:15,174
Sorry.

892
00:43:15,217 --> 00:43:16,468
It's okay. Um...

893
00:43:17,595 --> 00:43:20,347
Yoshi works at your parents' restaurant?

894
00:43:21,348 --> 00:43:24,768
Not exactly. You know,
he just picks up stuff sometimes.

895
00:43:24,852 --> 00:43:28,522
Uh-huh. And then
he sends them to food banks.

896
00:43:29,815 --> 00:43:30,815
Sometimes.

897
00:43:32,234 --> 00:43:33,234
[whispers] Sometimes.

898
00:43:34,153 --> 00:43:35,195
What's going on?

899
00:43:35,946 --> 00:43:40,034
All right. Uh, I've been making these
huge catering orders from Aroma

900
00:43:40,117 --> 00:43:44,705
and giving them to homeless shelters,
food banks, Little League teams. [scoffs]

901
00:43:45,205 --> 00:43:46,874
Okay, but why through Yoshi?

902
00:43:48,709 --> 00:43:49,709
My dad doesn't know.

903
00:43:50,252 --> 00:43:53,881
You're doing this behind his back.
That just feels wrong.

904
00:43:53,964 --> 00:43:57,176
The restaurant is struggling, you know?
And he's a stubborn man.

905
00:43:58,552 --> 00:43:59,386
Huh.

906
00:43:59,511 --> 00:44:01,096
Yeah, anyway. Let's eat.

907
00:44:06,518 --> 00:44:08,854
- I just have one question for you.
- Hmm?

908
00:44:08,937 --> 00:44:12,107
Would you like some mango pickle
with your quesalupa?

909
00:44:13,442 --> 00:44:14,568
You talking dirty to me?

910
00:44:14,652 --> 00:44:16,570
[Asha chuckles]

911
00:44:16,654 --> 00:44:19,365
["Key To Love (Is Understanding)"
playing from record player]

912
00:44:19,448 --> 00:44:22,034
I am stuffed.

913
00:44:22,117 --> 00:44:24,286
There's another quesalupa
with your name on it.

914
00:44:24,370 --> 00:44:25,663
<i>No mas</i> for me.

915
00:44:27,331 --> 00:44:28,332
[sighs]

916
00:44:32,753 --> 00:44:33,753
Shh.

917
00:44:34,546 --> 00:44:35,546
Listen.

918
00:44:37,174 --> 00:44:38,174
What is it?

919
00:44:38,842 --> 00:44:40,469
The sound of no aunties.

920
00:44:41,929 --> 00:44:42,929
No Yoshi.

921
00:44:43,972 --> 00:44:46,058
- No parents.
- Mm-hmm.

922
00:44:46,892 --> 00:44:48,435
Nobody left to fool.

923
00:44:48,519 --> 00:44:49,519
Huh.

924
00:44:51,939 --> 00:44:55,734
I could be making a big mistake
hanging out with, like, this cool DJ,

925
00:44:55,818 --> 00:44:59,405
who, like, drops beats,
turns tables, scratches things.

926
00:44:59,988 --> 00:45:01,073
Yeah, that's me.

927
00:45:01,156 --> 00:45:03,575
I talk a lot when nervous.
It's called logorrhea.

928
00:45:03,659 --> 00:45:05,160
- You might've heard of it.
- Right.

929
00:45:05,244 --> 00:45:08,455
It's... It's this really long word.
I don't know how to spell it...

930
00:45:09,915 --> 00:45:12,543
<i>♪ Key to love... ♪</i>

931
00:45:16,213 --> 00:45:18,006
Did you just kiss me?

932
00:45:19,299 --> 00:45:20,884
Looked like you could use a kiss.

933
00:45:20,968 --> 00:45:21,968
Hmm.

934
00:45:25,556 --> 00:45:27,099
Are we still role-playing?

935
00:45:30,394 --> 00:45:31,645
We're improvising.

936
00:45:34,440 --> 00:45:38,318
<i>♪ I just want to set them straight... ♪</i>

937
00:45:38,402 --> 00:45:39,402
Okay.

938
00:45:41,196 --> 00:45:46,326
<i>♪ They just don't seem
To understand about love these days... ♪</i>

939
00:45:46,410 --> 00:45:48,162
[scoffs] And I'm boring you. Wow.

940
00:45:48,245 --> 00:45:49,955
Sorry. It's not you.

941
00:45:50,038 --> 00:45:52,958
- Uh-huh. It's the music, right?
- Mm-mm.

942
00:45:53,041 --> 00:45:54,835
Yeah, better be the music.

943
00:45:56,837 --> 00:46:01,550
- What does a DJ actually do?
- I like to think I make people happy.

944
00:46:02,551 --> 00:46:03,677
Make people happy?

945
00:46:04,261 --> 00:46:07,890
Mm-hmm. I connect with people.
I can feel their energy, you know?

946
00:46:07,973 --> 00:46:08,973
Mm.

947
00:46:09,016 --> 00:46:12,352
[Ravi] I can tell when their moods
are shifting. I can build on it.

948
00:46:12,936 --> 00:46:16,565
Music's just something
that brings people together, you know?

949
00:46:16,648 --> 00:46:21,403
I just love being a part of it.
When I was a kid, I used to feel so lost...

950
00:46:21,487 --> 00:46:23,655
