That's literally what this is.

1203
01:00:13,318 --> 01:00:14,402
[Priya sighs]

1204
01:00:14,485 --> 01:00:15,987
Wow, London. That's, um...

1205
01:00:16,070 --> 01:00:18,323
A once-in-a-lifetime opportunity.

1206
01:00:18,906 --> 01:00:19,906
Thanks, Dad.

1207
01:00:19,949 --> 01:00:24,746
But look. If you're going to go so far
at least get engaged first.

1208
01:00:24,829 --> 01:00:25,830
- Mom!
- [Dinesh] I agree.

1209
01:00:25,913 --> 01:00:28,333
I could check their horoscopes next week.

1210
01:00:28,416 --> 01:00:30,084
No horoscope, none of this nonsense.

1211
01:00:30,168 --> 01:00:33,087
I agree. They care for each other.
That's all that matters.

1212
01:00:33,171 --> 01:00:38,301
Yeah. And Ravi, we know you are a kind,
decent, honest boy. Hmm?

1213
01:00:38,968 --> 01:00:44,057
Okay, Auntie, it's nice that you say that,
but I... I need to tell you something.

1214
01:00:44,140 --> 01:00:46,351
- Like, all of you.
- [coughs]

1215
01:00:46,434 --> 01:00:48,394
Ravi. [chokes]

1216
01:00:48,478 --> 01:00:49,687
- Dad?
- Dinesh?

1217
01:00:49,771 --> 01:00:52,023
- Are you okay?
- Get some water.

1218
01:00:52,106 --> 01:00:53,149
Are you okay?

1219
01:00:53,232 --> 01:00:56,861
Ravi, don't say anything.
It's your last chance to be happy!

1220
01:00:57,528 --> 01:00:59,238
- Try to relax.
- Quickly, quickly!

1221
01:00:59,322 --> 01:01:00,156
I'm okay.

1222
01:01:00,239 --> 01:01:02,325
Guys, he's fine. He panicked.

1223
01:01:02,408 --> 01:01:05,453
Relax, Dinesh.
They'll get married in their own time.

1224
01:01:05,536 --> 01:01:07,497
- Dad, stop it.
- Whiskey.

1225
01:01:07,580 --> 01:01:09,791
Okay. Uncle,
that's not the reason he panicked.

1226
01:01:09,874 --> 01:01:13,753
He panicked 'cause I was gonna tell you
that my biodata, it's all lies.

1227
01:01:13,836 --> 01:01:16,255
But who cares? So is mine. Everyone's is.

1228
01:01:16,339 --> 01:01:18,091
Yeah, but Asha, mine is, like...

1229
01:01:18,174 --> 01:01:21,761
Yeah, but you did go to MIT.
You do run your own company.

1230
01:01:21,844 --> 01:01:24,389
Okay, come on, Dad.
Yeah, I went to MIT. Okay.

1231
01:01:24,472 --> 01:01:27,141
I was 16 years old.
I didn't know what I was doing.

1232
01:01:29,769 --> 01:01:31,479
So I dropped out, by the way.

1233
01:01:35,441 --> 01:01:38,361
That must've been very difficult.
When did you go back?

1234
01:01:39,404 --> 01:01:40,947
I didn't go back, Uncle.

1235
01:01:41,864 --> 01:01:44,200
I couldn't. I just...

1236
01:01:44,283 --> 01:01:48,329
I needed time to figure out what I wanted,
without all the pressure.

1237
01:01:48,413 --> 01:01:49,497
And that time, it...

1238
01:01:50,790 --> 01:01:51,833
It saved my life.

1239
01:01:54,335 --> 01:01:56,421
So, yeah, I didn't finish college.

1240
01:01:58,965 --> 01:02:00,425
But I do have a company.

1241
01:02:01,676 --> 01:02:04,137
It's just not a start-up. I'm a DJ.

1242
01:02:04,220 --> 01:02:06,013
- [Nick scoffs]
- [in Hindi] <i>Hai raam.</i>

1243
01:02:06,431 --> 01:02:07,265
Oh.

1244
01:02:07,348 --> 01:02:09,016
[Vijay in English] It's okay.

1245
01:02:09,100 --> 01:02:10,852
Why didn't you just tell me?

1246
01:02:11,519 --> 01:02:12,687
Asha, I tried to.

1247
01:02:12,770 --> 01:02:16,107
He should've come clean way sooner,
but it's not a big deal.

1248
01:02:16,190 --> 01:02:18,860
- When we found out, it...
- You and Nick knew about this?

1249
01:02:18,943 --> 01:02:20,319
My buddy Joby told me, yeah.

1250
01:02:20,403 --> 01:02:22,864
You didn't think
it was important to tell me?

1251
01:02:22,947 --> 01:02:24,615
Because we like him.

1252
01:02:25,324 --> 01:02:26,324
Right?

1253
01:02:26,826 --> 01:02:29,287
Oh yeah, no, we like him. Oh yeah, a lot.

1254
01:02:30,288 --> 01:02:33,291
Wait a minute.
Ravi, you had 15 years to make it right?

1255
01:02:33,374 --> 01:02:35,501
Go back to school, get a job, but...

1256
01:02:36,085 --> 01:02:38,379
[scoffs] You become a DJ?

1257
01:02:38,463 --> 01:02:41,215
Ravi, can this lifestyle support a family?

1258
01:02:41,299 --> 01:02:43,299
Dad, don't ask him that.
We're not getting engaged.

1259
01:02:43,342 --> 01:02:44,510
Yeah, Uncle, I can.

1260
01:02:44,594 --> 01:02:46,679
[Asha] And why are you even responding?

1261
01:02:46,763 --> 01:02:50,224
I don't need anyone to support me.
Why is this always about supporting me?

1262
01:02:50,308 --> 01:02:53,728
Even if I wanted a family,
I could do it on my own.

1263
01:02:54,312 --> 01:02:57,815
All I would really like is some honesty.

1264
01:02:57,899 --> 01:03:01,736
But Asha, wasn't it your idea to pretend
to be a couple in the first place?

1265
01:03:01,819 --> 01:03:03,362
- [mothers] What?
- Oh my God.

1266
01:03:03,446 --> 01:03:04,614
You lied to us, Asha?

1267
01:03:04,697 --> 01:03:05,990
How could you do this?

1268
01:03:06,073 --> 01:03:07,116
Because of this!

1269
01:03:07,992 --> 01:03:13,122
Because you people drive us insane
with your pressure. This is what happens!

1270
01:03:14,165 --> 01:03:15,458
We are dating now, though.

1271
01:03:15,541 --> 01:03:19,796
What's the point of that? You're a DJ.
How will you pay for your kids' college?

1272
01:03:19,879 --> 01:03:21,672
- Mom...
- Anyone smell the...

1273
01:03:21,756 --> 01:03:23,591
'Cause it smells like burning, so...

1274
01:03:23,674 --> 01:03:27,261
I told you! No one wants to marry
a bum like you. Now do you see?

1275
01:03:27,345 --> 01:03:28,596
Don't call my son a bum!

1276
01:03:28,679 --> 01:03:29,680
You encouraged this!

1277
01:03:29,764 --> 01:03:30,765
Okay, Dad, stop.

1278
01:03:31,265 --> 01:03:35,144
Let me ask you. Who do you think paid for
all the catering orders these last months?

1279
01:03:35,228 --> 01:03:38,231
- What?
- Food banks, homeless shelters, the teams.

1280
01:03:38,314 --> 01:03:42,318
- What are you talking about?
- Red Star Standard, Dad. Ring a bell?

1281
01:03:42,401 --> 01:03:43,820
[Dinesh] What about it?

1282
01:03:43,903 --> 01:03:47,406
Those are my initials, Dad.
That's me, I'm Red Star Standard.

1283
01:03:48,199 --> 01:03:49,408
Red Star Standard?

1284
01:03:51,702 --> 01:03:52,702
That's you?

1285
01:03:53,120 --> 01:03:55,373
Yeah. It's this charitable fund I just...

1286
01:03:55,456 --> 01:03:56,499
[whispers] Oh my God.

1287
01:03:56,999 --> 01:03:58,751
- Asha...
- [smoke detector beeping]

1288
01:03:58,835 --> 01:04:02,588
[breathes heavily]
No one panic. The aloo gobi's on fire.

1289
01:04:02,672 --> 01:04:04,382
[Suneeta] What? Aloo gobi?

1290
01:04:04,465 --> 01:04:05,967
- Asha, wait.
- [Suneeta] Oh my God!

1291
01:04:06,050 --> 01:04:07,802
[Asha] Did it ever occur to you to ask?

1292
01:04:07,885 --> 01:04:09,262
Why are you so upset?

1293
01:04:09,345 --> 01:04:12,473
Oh. [scoffs] How many more surprises
do you have for me?

1294
01:04:13,266 --> 01:04:14,706
I thought this would make you happy.

1295
01:04:14,767 --> 01:04:18,479
"You have to own what you want and trust
your inner voice?" What the hell?

1296
01:04:18,563 --> 01:04:19,564
I meant it.

1297
01:04:19,647 --> 01:04:21,774
But you don't think
I can do my job on my own.

1298
01:04:21,858 --> 01:04:24,569
Asha, you convinced me
it was a good investment...

1299
01:04:24,652 --> 01:04:28,614
I wasn't trying to convince <i>you.</i>
I needed to do this by myself.

1300
01:04:28,698 --> 01:04:30,032
I just wanted to help.

1301
01:04:30,116 --> 01:04:31,116
Help?

1302
01:04:32,827 --> 01:04:36,289
The way you helped your dad?
Don't you see that it's so patronizing?

1303
01:04:37,331 --> 01:04:39,083
How do you even have so much money?

1304
01:04:39,166 --> 01:04:41,836
Rob a bank? Sell endangered species
off the back of a van.

1305
01:04:41,919 --> 01:04:43,588
No, it's because of Facebook.

1306
01:04:43,671 --> 01:04:45,965
- So you did work at a start-up.
- Not exactly.

1307
01:04:46,048 --> 01:04:48,819
I DJ'd a couple parties for them
back in the day and they couldn't pay.

1308
01:04:48,843 --> 01:04:50,052
Gave me stock instead.

1309
01:04:50,136 --> 01:04:52,597
You made a million bucks
DJing some nerd parties?

1310
01:04:52,680 --> 01:04:55,725
A lot more, actually.
Look, it's no big deal.

1311
01:04:55,808 --> 01:04:58,227
It is a big deal. I am not some cause.

1312
01:04:58,311 --> 01:04:59,896
I know that, Asha. I know that.

1313
01:04:59,979 --> 01:05:02,982
At least Krish was honest about the fact
that he didn't believe in me.

1314
01:05:03,065 --> 01:05:05,526
- You did it behind my back.
- Seriously?

1315
01:05:06,903 --> 01:05:09,989
Let me ask. You ever been honest
about a single relationship?

1316
01:05:10,072 --> 01:05:12,283
- Don't turn this around.
- You wanted to role-play.

1317
01:05:12,366 --> 01:05:13,743
Yeah, and you broke character.

1318
01:05:16,579 --> 01:05:18,039
[emotional music playing]

1319
01:05:18,122 --> 01:05:20,917
There is a big difference
between telling a white lie

1320
01:05:21,000 --> 01:05:22,835
and being completely untruthful.

1321
01:05:25,421 --> 01:05:26,464
Who even are you?

1322
01:05:27,256 --> 01:05:30,426
Asha, I'm the guy
who went to 14 weddings with you.

1323
01:05:32,261 --> 01:05:35,723
Not because I had to.
Not because my parents forced me to.

1324
01:05:35,806 --> 01:05:38,142
I went because I genuinely wanted to.

1325
01:05:39,477 --> 01:05:41,729
That's the only thing
I was untruthful about.

1326
01:05:41,812 --> 01:05:44,065
That I didn't have to pretend to be
in love with you.

1327
01:05:44,148 --> 01:05:46,150
Which is what I am, by the way.

1328
01:05:48,402 --> 01:05:49,695
I'm in love with you.

1329
01:05:56,243 --> 01:05:58,204
I opened my heart to you, Ravi.

1330
01:06:02,333 --> 01:06:04,043
Do you know what that took?

1331
01:06:09,298 --> 01:06:10,633
And for the record,

1332
01:06:12,009 --> 01:06:13,427
I don't care about MIT.

1333
01:06:17,056 --> 01:06:18,933
I trusted you, and you let me down.

1334
01:06:29,318 --> 01:06:30,318
[sighs]

1335
01:06:46,460 --> 01:06:47,545
Hey, Mom.

1336
01:06:48,421 --> 01:06:52,049
I can't believe it, <i>beta.</i> You spent
thousands on orders through Red Star.

1337
01:06:52,550 --> 01:06:55,052
He wouldn't let me help you otherwise, so...

1338
01:06:56,137 --> 01:06:59,557
You were always different,
even as a child.

1339
01:07:01,475 --> 01:07:02,935
And I worried for you.

1340
01:07:04,687 --> 01:07:06,647
Mom, what was the point in lying?

1341
01:07:07,732 --> 01:07:10,568
Asha and her parents
want nothing to do with me now.

1342
01:07:12,194 --> 01:07:13,946
We were only trying to help.

1343
01:07:14,530 --> 01:07:18,617
Do not blame your mom.
You met Asha because of that biodata.

1344
01:07:18,701 --> 01:07:20,119
Can't you see?

1345
01:07:20,619 --> 01:07:24,790
You're our son. We would lie, die,
whatever for your happiness.

1346
01:07:24,874 --> 01:07:26,834
Yeah, Dad, but I <i>was </i>happy.

1347
01:07:26,917 --> 01:07:28,794
Then you should've kept your mouth shut.

1348
01:07:31,672 --> 01:07:32,672
Talk to her.

1349
01:07:33,299 --> 01:07:35,551
- She won't take my calls.
- Then go to her.

1350
01:07:36,260 --> 01:07:37,845
[sighs] It doesn't matter.

1351
01:07:39,805 --> 01:07:41,724
I came to tell you I'm going back to work.

1352
01:07:42,349 --> 01:07:44,393
Yoshi lined up
a bunch of gigs, and I just...

1353
01:07:45,519 --> 01:07:47,480
- I think it's time.
- Ravi, no.

1354
01:07:47,563 --> 01:07:52,234
Mom, I am done lying.
I'm done pretending to be someone I'm not.

1355
01:07:52,318 --> 01:07:55,196
Again, you're running away
the minute things get hard. [scoffs]

1356
01:07:55,279 --> 01:07:57,948
Okay. Here's the thing, Dad.

1357
01:07:58,449 --> 01:08:00,659
I am not running away.

1358
01:08:01,202 --> 01:08:04,121
Okay? This is my job. This is who I am.

1359
01:08:04,914 --> 01:08:08,793
I just wish you could see that.
I wish that was enough, but clearly not...

1360
01:08:08,876 --> 01:08:10,836
Ravi, it's not that. We want you...

1361
01:08:10,920 --> 01:08:14,799
We want the son we lost when
he dropped out of MIT and disappeared.

1362
01:08:16,133 --> 01:08:19,887
- We want those years back.
- Yeah, but those years are gone, Dad!

1363
01:08:19,970 --> 01:08:21,347
Those years are gone!

1364
01:08:23,641 --> 01:08:28,145
But the son you do have is standing
right in front of you. I am right here.

1365
01:08:32,066 --> 01:08:33,776
[melancholic music playing]

1366
01:08:33,859 --> 01:08:34,859
Okay.

1367
01:09:52,938 --> 01:09:54,940
I recommend a flat in Shoreditch.

1368
01:09:55,024 --> 01:09:58,611
It's murderously expensive,
but you're getting a raise.

1369
01:10:07,786 --> 01:10:09,663
They called again to see if you'd signed.

1370
01:10:10,581 --> 01:10:11,581
[phone chimes]

1371
01:10:17,004 --> 01:10:20,341
Ash, he's an international DJ.
You'll see him again.

1372
01:10:21,550 --> 01:10:22,635
I don't think so.

1373
01:10:23,219 --> 01:10:25,054
Look. I'm sorry. I'm confused.

1374
01:10:25,846 --> 01:10:29,642
This guy that you pretended to date
and thought was broke,

1375
01:10:29,725 --> 01:10:31,560
you actually fell in love with.

1376
01:10:32,478 --> 01:10:34,897
Okay. And, it turns out,
oh, he's crazy rich.

1377
01:10:35,397 --> 01:10:37,942
Not to mention, he helped you get promoted
over your boss.

1378
01:10:38,025 --> 01:10:39,401
He believes in you.

1379
01:10:39,485 --> 01:10:42,196
And this is the guy
you never wanna see again.

1380
01:10:44,657 --> 01:10:47,826
You need to swallow your pride
you need to sign that contract,

1381
01:10:47,910 --> 01:10:51,330
and then you need to apologize
to that boy. It is that simple.

1382
01:10:51,413 --> 01:10:53,165
- It's not...
- I don't wanna hear it!

1383
01:10:54,583 --> 01:10:55,960
You know what's not simple?

1384
01:10:57,753 --> 01:10:58,753
Seeing you go.

1385
01:11:01,590 --> 01:11:02,800
I'm gonna miss you.

1386
01:11:02,883 --> 01:11:04,218
We're gonna miss you.

1387
01:11:04,301 --> 01:11:08,264
I'm gonna hate your phony British accent
you're obviously gonna come home with.

1388
01:11:10,891 --> 01:11:13,477
But if you let opportunities
like this pass you by...

1389
01:11:16,188 --> 01:11:18,274
- I'm gonna have to kill you.
- [Asha chuckles]

1390
01:11:18,357 --> 01:11:20,567
I know people in this town
who can make that happen.

1391
01:11:20,651 --> 01:11:23,612
- Okay.
- If it's really over, why not just go?

1392
01:11:23,696 --> 01:11:24,905
What's holding you back?

1393
01:11:26,156 --> 01:11:31,495
I guess my family, my parents, my sister.
I've never left them like this before.

1394
01:11:31,578 --> 01:11:35,291
We spend so much energy
trying to get away from our parents.

1395
01:11:35,374 --> 01:11:37,501
And when we finally get the chance...

1396
01:11:38,002 --> 01:11:39,586
[emotional music playing]

1397
01:11:39,670 --> 01:11:42,172
It was hard for me
to leave Jamaica for London.

1398
01:11:43,674 --> 01:11:47,720
I didn't want to abandon my parents.
In spite of our differences.

1399
01:11:48,304 --> 01:11:49,471
And how did you?

1400
01:11:49,555 --> 01:11:53,142
I realized my life is where I take it.

1401
01:11:54,435 --> 01:11:56,770
My parents will always be there for me.

1402
01:11:56,854 --> 01:12:01,108
But opportunities like these
don't come along every day.

1403
01:12:04,737 --> 01:12:07,448
So this is where you're saving the world.

1404
01:12:08,115 --> 01:12:10,326
- Dad?
- [exhales] We were just leaving.

1405
01:12:15,122 --> 01:12:16,122
Mr. Maurya.

1406
01:12:16,915 --> 01:12:18,459
What are you doing here?

1407
01:12:20,878 --> 01:12:22,546
You want to go for a walk?

1408
01:12:25,174 --> 01:12:27,176
[hopeful music playing]

1409
01:12:31,555 --> 01:12:37,144
<i>Beta, </i>when I was a young economist,
it was a different time.

1410
01:12:38,312 --> 01:12:41,523
White men half as smart as me
would get promoted above me.

1411
01:12:41,607 --> 01:12:43,859
I'd get stuck doing their job for them.

1412
01:12:44,943 --> 01:12:48,947
You know what my boss said?
He said, "Indians? They're smart, sure,

1413
01:12:49,031 --> 01:12:52,159
but they're numbers guys.
They'll never be leaders."

1414
01:12:52,951 --> 01:12:57,331
I know. Makes me so mad.
I'm sorry you had to go through that, Dad.

1415
01:12:57,414 --> 01:13:01,168
Which is why I was so worried
that you were being too idealistic.

1416
01:13:01,668 --> 01:13:04,713
I didn't want you to face
the same disappointment I had.

1417
01:13:06,590 --> 01:13:08,717
But, um, look at you.

1418
01:13:10,219 --> 01:13:11,387
You did it.

1419
01:13:13,722 --> 01:13:16,016
Bigger numbers than I ever dreamt of.

1420
01:13:16,725 --> 01:13:17,725
[Asha chuckles]

1421
01:13:17,768 --> 01:13:19,895
And you know what makes me the most proud?

1422
01:13:20,979 --> 01:13:22,981
That you did it on your own terms.

1423
01:13:23,941 --> 01:13:26,902
<i>Jah, beti.</i> Go to London. You deserve it.

1424
01:13:27,444 --> 01:13:30,948
- [sighs]
- Go have the experience of a lifetime.

1425
01:13:32,366 --> 01:13:33,575
For me.

1426
01:13:38,205 --> 01:13:40,165
I'm sorry that I lied to you.

1427
01:13:41,458 --> 01:13:42,918
I'm sorry we drove you crazy.

1428
01:13:44,878 --> 01:13:47,131
- I blame it on your mother.
- [Asha giggles]

1429
01:13:50,008 --> 01:13:52,344
I think I have time for some ice cream.

1430
01:13:52,845 --> 01:13:54,388
What kind of job is this?

1431
01:14:06,483 --> 01:14:08,485
[soft emotional music playing]

1432
01:14:15,868 --> 01:14:17,870
[inaudible chatter]

1433
01:14:20,998 --> 01:14:23,542
<i>Offo,</i> where is your sister?

1434
01:14:23,625 --> 01:14:25,294
Getting her makeup done. Relax.

1435
01:14:25,377 --> 01:14:28,380
<i>Hai Bhagwan.</i>
Why is she only wearing one necklace?

1436
01:14:29,339 --> 01:14:31,133
'Cause she's not Mr. T, Ma.

1437
01:14:31,717 --> 01:14:36,013
Well, she's late now. Call and see
what time they left their home.

1438
01:14:36,638 --> 01:14:38,932
Their home? What do you mean "their home"?

1439
01:14:39,016 --> 01:14:43,103
You think I was born yesterday.
I know about the boyfriends.

1440
01:14:43,187 --> 01:14:45,397
The sneaking around at night.

1441
01:14:46,106 --> 01:14:48,400
And the fact that
Nick and Priya live together.

1442
01:14:49,276 --> 01:14:52,863
And yet you didn't say anything.
That is very unlike you.

1443
01:14:52,946 --> 01:14:57,784
I wanted her to tell me. I wanted
my daughters to tell me everything.

1444
01:15:00,579 --> 01:15:04,875
Well, you know, Ma,
that we've always wanted to.

1445
01:15:06,793 --> 01:15:08,003
We just didn't know how.

1446
01:15:09,129 --> 01:15:12,132
We never really speak
about that stuff in our family.

1447
01:15:13,759 --> 01:15:16,970
You never really even told me
about your life before I was born.

1448
01:15:18,013 --> 01:15:21,683
What is there to tell?
I drove my parents crazy, just like you.

1449
01:15:22,309 --> 01:15:24,561
I find that very hard to believe.

1450
01:15:25,854 --> 01:15:29,316
- I also know you found that photo.
- Of you and that boy?

1451
01:15:29,399 --> 01:15:30,400
[chuckles]

1452
01:15:31,735 --> 01:15:34,905
Parag and I were neighbors.
Our fathers were old friends.

1453
01:15:34,988 --> 01:15:37,366
When Parag would come for tea
with his father,

1454
01:15:37,449 --> 01:15:40,410
we would sit in the garden
and talk for hours.

1455
01:15:40,994 --> 01:15:42,871
Of course, we fell in love.

1456
01:15:44,248 --> 01:15:47,793
When it came time to arrange my marriage,
I told my parents about him,

1457
01:15:48,335 --> 01:15:49,211
but they forbade it.

1458
01:15:49,294 --> 01:15:52,965
He was from a different caste, they said.

1459
01:15:54,466 --> 01:15:57,469
My father never spoke
to Parag's family again.

1460
01:16:00,305 --> 01:16:04,935
My parents arranged a <i>shaadi </i>for me
to your father and my fate was sealed.

1461
01:16:07,187 --> 01:16:08,187
Mom.

1462
01:16:11,817 --> 01:16:13,944
That must have been so heartbreaking.

1463
01:16:14,987 --> 01:16:15,987
It was.

1464
01:16:16,488 --> 01:16:19,741
[chuckles] At first,
I pretended to love your dad.

1465
01:16:19,825 --> 01:16:23,370
But eventually,
I didn't need to pretend anymore.

1466
01:16:25,539 --> 01:16:29,751
And now I have you girls
and this beautiful life.

1467
01:16:34,006 --> 01:16:35,674
Do you ever think about him?

1468
01:16:36,508 --> 01:16:38,677
Oh yeah, from time to time.

1469
01:16:38,760 --> 01:16:42,389
I told myself, if I ever had daughters,
I would let them choose their fate,

1470
01:16:42,472 --> 01:16:43,557
their happiness.

1471
01:16:44,266 --> 01:16:49,730
Yeah, as long as we have five MBAs,
choose a nice guy, and make round rotis.

1472
01:16:49,813 --> 01:16:52,816
- This looks good. You should wear this.
- This isn't <i>Game of Thrones.</i>

1473
01:16:52,899 --> 01:16:56,486
Listen to you, Miss Taco Bell.
When have you even made one roti?

1474
01:16:56,570 --> 01:16:59,114
- I made, like, a quarter once.
- Yeah, once.

1475
01:17:00,324 --> 01:17:04,286
Oh, <i>beta.</i> I hate to see you go to London.

1476
01:17:05,912 --> 01:17:08,206
But that is your fate.

1477
01:17:09,499 --> 01:17:15,756
And darling, I know Ravi's not perfect,
but I feel he's your happiness.

1478
01:17:16,381 --> 01:17:18,258
I see the way he looks at you.

1479
01:17:18,342 --> 01:17:21,386
It's exactly the same way
your father's looked at me

1480
01:17:21,470 --> 01:17:23,013
since the day we met.

1481
01:17:27,309 --> 01:17:29,936
- Why are you sitting around? Priya's gone!
- What?

1482
01:17:30,020 --> 01:17:32,100
She's didn't show up for makeup
and her phone is off.

1483
01:17:32,147 --> 01:17:34,232
She was supposed to do that an hour ago.

1484
01:17:34,316 --> 01:17:37,194
Calm down. She's gotta be here somewhere.
Let's split up.

1485
01:17:37,277 --> 01:17:38,320
Should've had sons.

1486
01:17:38,403 --> 01:17:40,113
Vijay, call 911!

1487
01:17:40,197 --> 01:17:42,491
- I go this way, you that way.
- Yeah, okay.

1488
01:17:42,574 --> 01:17:43,992
- Priya?
- [Vijay] Priya?

1489
01:17:44,534 --> 01:17:46,119
- [women shriek]
- Ah! Sorry, Aunties.

1490
01:17:46,203 --> 01:17:47,537
[rhythmic music playing]

1491
01:17:47,621 --> 01:17:48,621
Priya!

1492
01:17:49,748 --> 01:17:50,832
- Pri!
- Darling?

1493
01:17:51,333 --> 01:17:54,378
- [occupant yells]
- Sorry! How many bathrooms are there?

1494
01:17:54,461 --> 01:17:56,046
Priya? Priya, <i>beta!</i>

1495
01:17:56,129 --> 01:17:58,715
Don't worry, everything's fine. Priya!

1496
01:18:00,008 --> 01:18:01,134
- Asha.
- Nick?

1497
01:18:01,218 --> 01:18:02,928
- I need help.
- Have you seen Priya?

1498
01:18:03,011 --> 01:18:03,845
- Priya?
- Yes!

1499
01:18:03,929 --> 01:18:07,140
- No. Wait, I need your...
- [groans] Priya! Pri?

1500
01:18:08,600 --> 01:18:09,600
Pri?

1501
01:18:11,061 --> 01:18:13,188
- Pri, is that you?
- [Priya] No. [sobs]

1502
01:18:13,271 --> 01:18:15,524
- Want to talk about it?
- [Priya] No!

1503
01:18:15,607 --> 01:18:19,444
Uh, okay, I don't mean to rush you,
but your guests have started to arrive.

1504
01:18:19,528 --> 01:18:20,987
[Priya] I don't care!

1505
01:18:21,571 --> 01:18:23,323
Come on, open up. It's only me.

1506
01:18:23,407 --> 01:18:24,783
[Priya] It's fricking open.

1507
01:18:25,534 --> 01:18:27,536
Oh. [sighs]

1508
01:18:28,328 --> 01:18:30,414
- What is going on here?
- [grunts]

1509
01:18:30,497 --> 01:18:33,750
I didn't want the ice sculptures.
I didn't...

1510
01:18:33,834 --> 01:18:38,171
I didn't want the gold-leaf cake,
and why can't he just wear a tuxedo?

1511
01:18:38,255 --> 01:18:41,800
Okay, Dr. Priya, time for a little chat.

1512
01:18:41,883 --> 01:18:44,678
He won't even tell me
what his big surprise is.

1513
01:18:44,761 --> 01:18:47,180
Then it wouldn't be a surprise, would it?

1514
01:18:47,889 --> 01:18:52,519
I don't think this is about cakes
or ice sculptures or surprises.

1515
01:18:52,602 --> 01:18:56,064
- I think this is about you.
- How is this possibly about me?

1516
01:18:56,148 --> 01:18:59,443
For some reason, I think
this whole seven lifetimes thing

1517
01:18:59,526 --> 01:19:00,986
has you kind of freaked out.

1518
01:19:04,698 --> 01:19:06,283
It just got me thinking.

1519
01:19:06,366 --> 01:19:09,745
Every generation in our family
has done this for centuries.

1520
01:19:10,454 --> 01:19:12,664
What if I'm the first one to screw it up?

1521
01:19:13,915 --> 01:19:15,835
You don't have to worry.
I already screwed it up.

1522
01:19:15,876 --> 01:19:18,920
But I'm the first one to marry someone
who isn't Indian.

1523
01:19:19,004 --> 01:19:22,007
Is that what this is about? 'Cause Nick is
way more Indian than we are.

1524
01:19:22,090 --> 01:19:26,344
Are you seriously gonna say that to me?
How's that supposed to make me feel...

1525
01:19:26,428 --> 01:19:28,054
I know. Listen, listen, listen.

1526
01:19:28,972 --> 01:19:32,267
- [sobs]
- Nick is crazy about you.

1527
01:19:33,018 --> 01:19:36,605
Okay? I mean, otherwise
he wouldn't be dressed the way he is.

1528
01:19:37,189 --> 01:19:38,982
- How's he dressed?
- Doesn't matter.

1529
01:19:39,065 --> 01:19:41,443
What matters is that he loves you.

1530
01:19:41,526 --> 01:19:42,819
[sighs]

1531
01:19:42,903 --> 01:19:44,613
And Mom and Dad love him.

1532
01:19:45,280 --> 01:19:47,365
Or at least, they will learn to.

1533
01:19:49,409 --> 01:19:52,037
The only question that remains is, do you?

1534
01:19:52,537 --> 01:19:54,539
[emotional music playing]

1535
01:19:57,834 --> 01:19:59,503
But I'm scared.

1536
01:20:03,048 --> 01:20:04,549
We're all scared.

1537
01:20:07,427 --> 01:20:09,054
If you don't marry Nick today,

1538
01:20:09,137 --> 01:20:11,890
you're gonna regret it
for the rest of your life.

1539
01:20:14,768 --> 01:20:18,355
Pri, you have a chance
to live your life the way you want to.

1540
01:20:20,190 --> 01:20:21,900
So just tune out the noise.

1541
01:20:23,109 --> 01:20:24,528
Listen to your heart.

1542
01:20:26,780 --> 01:20:28,949
Let your love be greater than your fear.

1543
01:20:33,495 --> 01:20:35,455
[chuckles] That's beautiful, Ash.

1544
01:20:36,832 --> 01:20:39,334
- Did you come up with that yourself?
- Yep.

1545
01:20:40,627 --> 01:20:41,627
No.

1546
01:20:43,797 --> 01:20:44,797
[chuckles]

1547
01:20:46,216 --> 01:20:48,260
It was someone
a little bit smarter than me.

1548
01:20:51,012 --> 01:20:53,014
We need to get you into makeup. Now.

1549
01:20:53,098 --> 01:20:55,976
- Really?
- Yes, really. You should see your face.

1550
01:20:56,059 --> 01:20:57,060
God!

1551
01:20:57,143 --> 01:21:00,981
Priya! Thank God!
Quickly, let's get you ready and dressed.

1552
01:21:01,064 --> 01:21:02,566
- Have you been drinking?
- No.

1553
01:21:02,649 --> 01:21:04,234
Yes. Get her some coffee.

1554
01:21:04,317 --> 01:21:06,152
Wait, wait, no. Let's get you dressed.

1555
01:21:06,236 --> 01:21:07,779
There's something I need to do first.

1556
01:21:07,863 --> 01:21:09,781
- Where you going?
- Don't worry, I'll be back.

1557
01:21:09,865 --> 01:21:12,868
<i>Hai raam!</i>
I can smell the Pinot Grigio on you.

1558
01:21:12,951 --> 01:21:14,160
[tires screeching]

1559
01:21:14,244 --> 01:21:16,246
[tense music playing]

1560
01:21:21,501 --> 01:21:22,669
[laughter]

1561
01:21:22,752 --> 01:21:25,088
- I know. I was 12 years old.
- Oh my God.

1562
01:21:25,171 --> 01:21:28,633
And so, I'm alone with this person
who's driving me crazy.

1563
01:21:28,717 --> 01:21:31,136
I had to walk home. Can you imagine that?

1564
01:21:32,345 --> 01:21:34,806
- And I decided to keep it.
- Ravi?

1565
01:21:36,182 --> 01:21:40,353
- Asha. What're you doing here?
- I was an idiot. I owe you an apology.

1566
01:21:40,437 --> 01:21:41,605
Asha, you don't have to...

1567
01:21:41,688 --> 01:21:46,693
I never had a chance to thank you.
For going along with my crazy scheme.

1568
01:21:46,776 --> 01:21:50,030
[emotional music playing]

1569
01:21:50,113 --> 01:21:54,200
For teaching me how to drop beats
and turn tables.

1570
01:21:56,036 --> 01:21:59,331
For donating 50 years' worth
of Indian takeout to my work.

1571
01:21:59,414 --> 01:22:00,414
[chuckles]

1572
01:22:02,292 --> 01:22:04,002
I know it came from your heart.

1573
01:22:05,837 --> 01:22:08,048
Because everything you do
comes from your heart.

1574
01:22:12,427 --> 01:22:15,347
[inhales] And I was wrong to say
you didn't believe in me.

1575
01:22:19,059 --> 01:22:20,143
[whispers] I'm sorry.

1576
01:22:20,644 --> 01:22:21,644
Ash...

1577
01:22:21,978 --> 01:22:24,606
Um, Ravi, who is this?

1578
01:22:24,689 --> 01:22:25,689
[Asha] Doesn't matter.

1579
01:22:26,483 --> 01:22:29,319
What matters is this is a great guy,
you know?

1580
01:22:30,028 --> 01:22:32,948
He's brilliant. He's kind.
He's a true original.

1581
01:22:34,074 --> 01:22:36,409
He might seem like
a bit of a slacker at first.

1582
01:22:36,493 --> 01:22:37,994
I thought so too.

1583
01:22:38,745 --> 01:22:42,207
And you should never play him
at Bananagrams. Ever.

1584
01:22:44,960 --> 01:22:47,087
As you get to know him, he grows on you.

1585
01:22:48,588 --> 01:22:50,340
And if you're not too blind,

1586
01:22:51,841 --> 01:22:54,803
you'll find he's the kind of guy
you want cheering you on.

1587
01:22:58,181 --> 01:22:59,181
Always.

1588
01:23:00,850 --> 01:23:01,893
Ash.

1589
01:23:02,477 --> 01:23:03,728
- Asha.
- [woman] Go.

1590
01:23:03,812 --> 01:23:05,522
- Go!
- Asha!

1591
01:23:07,190 --> 01:23:08,900
It's not what you think!

1592
01:23:08,984 --> 01:23:10,068
Asha. Asha, wait!

1593
01:23:14,823 --> 01:23:17,742
- [Vijay] Everything's gonna be fine.
- Why do you keep saying that?

1594
01:23:17,826 --> 01:23:20,453
Why do you keep telling me to calm down.
This is serious.

1595
01:23:20,537 --> 01:23:21,705
People are listening.

1596
01:23:21,788 --> 01:23:23,623
- Why are we here?
- Thank God you're here.

1597
01:23:23,707 --> 01:23:25,375
Great. Now we need the groom.

1598
01:23:25,458 --> 01:23:26,292
Where's Nick?

1599
01:23:26,376 --> 01:23:28,294
- You haven't seen him?
- No. Why?

1600
01:23:28,378 --> 01:23:29,587
This is a disaster!

1601
01:23:29,671 --> 01:23:31,840
If this is his surprise,
this is not funny.

1602
01:23:31,923 --> 01:23:34,926
This white guy is taking
Indian Standard Time to a new level.

1603
01:23:35,010 --> 01:23:36,803
[Priya] How could he just disappear?

1604
01:23:36,886 --> 01:23:39,556
- I did see him before and he...
- He what?

1605
01:23:39,639 --> 01:23:40,849
He was asking for help.

1606
01:23:40,932 --> 01:23:42,702
- You didn't help him?
- I was looking for you!

1607
01:23:42,726 --> 01:23:45,478
- God, our daughters will never marry!
- Ma. Come on.

1608
01:23:45,562 --> 01:23:47,355
[traditional music playing]

1609
01:23:54,988 --> 01:23:56,990
[elephant trumpeting]

1610
01:23:57,073 --> 01:23:59,451
[guests cheering]

1611
01:24:04,456 --> 01:24:05,999
Is that an elephant?

1612
01:24:06,082 --> 01:24:08,084
- [elephant trumpeting]
- [Nick] Whoo!

1613
01:24:09,878 --> 01:24:10,920
[in Hindi]<i> Hai Bhagwan.</i>

1614
01:24:13,381 --> 01:24:16,384
[in English] Oh. My. God.

1615
01:24:30,482 --> 01:24:32,025
[in Hindi] Welcome, Spice Girls!

1616
01:24:32,108 --> 01:24:33,610
[guests laughing]

1617
01:24:37,363 --> 01:24:38,363
Priya.

1618
01:24:39,657 --> 01:24:41,409
[emotional music playing]

1619
01:24:41,493 --> 01:24:46,081
You are a dead onion.

1620
01:24:46,164 --> 01:24:47,749
[guests laughing]

1621
01:24:47,832 --> 01:24:53,296
With you, I'm a thin banana.

1622
01:24:56,299 --> 01:24:58,843
- [in English] Did I... I said...
- No.

1623
01:24:58,927 --> 01:25:00,804
- No?
- No.

1624
01:25:00,887 --> 01:25:03,014
My God, I'm so sorry I was so late.

1625
01:25:05,809 --> 01:25:09,229
I know you didn't want a whole thing,
and I did a whole thing.

1626
01:25:09,312 --> 01:25:10,313
It was perfect.

1627
01:25:10,396 --> 01:25:12,190
I love you so much.

1628
01:25:20,573 --> 01:25:22,408
[Asha] Come on, let's get you married!

1629
01:25:41,052 --> 01:25:43,054
[clapping and cheering]

1630
01:25:52,063 --> 01:25:53,231
[glasses clinking]

1631
01:25:53,314 --> 01:25:55,900
Congratulations, guys. Whoo!

1632
01:25:57,235 --> 01:26:01,281
And congratulations to my mom and dad too,
for staying out of their way.

1633
01:26:01,364 --> 01:26:02,740
- Mostly.
- Little bit.

1634
01:26:02,824 --> 01:26:03,950
[Asha sighs]

1635
01:26:04,033 --> 01:26:07,996
One thing that I have learned about love...

1636
01:26:09,998 --> 01:26:12,750
is that it's a lot
like moving to a new country.

1637
01:26:12,834 --> 01:26:16,713
Trying to build something
where nothing existed before.

1638
01:26:16,796 --> 01:26:18,298
[emotional music playing]

1639
01:26:18,381 --> 01:26:22,719
It's hanging on and letting go.

1640
01:26:23,344 --> 01:26:25,722
It's messy, it's beautiful,

1641
01:26:26,723 --> 01:26:28,725
like any giant leap of faith.

1642
01:26:31,102 --> 01:26:35,231
So congratulations to the two of you
for taking that leap.

1643
01:26:35,315 --> 01:26:38,318
May you take many more. I love you.

1644
01:26:40,028 --> 01:26:40,945
[Nick chuckles]

1645
01:26:41,029 --> 01:26:43,740
- Cheers to Nick and Priya!
- Cheers!

1646
01:26:43,823 --> 01:26:44,824
[guests cheering]

1647
01:26:45,450 --> 01:26:46,284
Cheers.

1648
01:26:46,367 --> 01:26:47,368
[Priya] Thank you.

1649
01:26:47,452 --> 01:26:48,661
Aw! You're welcome.

1650
01:26:48,745 --> 01:26:49,745
[Asha] I love you guys.

1651
01:26:49,787 --> 01:26:50,830
[Priya] Thank you, Ash.

1652
01:26:50,914 --> 01:26:52,040
You could get married too.

1653
01:26:52,123 --> 01:26:53,203
- [Priya] I love you.
- Mom!

1654
01:26:53,249 --> 01:26:58,671
And thank you to everyone
who celebrated with us today.

1655
01:26:59,547 --> 01:27:01,966
But we have a surprise for you.

1656
01:27:02,050 --> 01:27:03,801
I am honored to invite

1657
01:27:04,719 --> 01:27:08,264
our own DJ Spellbound!

1658
01:27:08,348 --> 01:27:10,850
[guests cheering]

1659
01:27:10,934 --> 01:27:11,934
That's Ravi!

1660
01:27:12,435 --> 01:27:14,145
Look, Asha, that's Ravi.

1661
01:27:14,229 --> 01:27:16,064
["Get It In" by Raja Kumari playing]

1662
01:27:16,147 --> 01:27:18,107
<i>♪ I think y'all know ♪</i>

1663
01:27:18,191 --> 01:27:20,902
<i>♪ Hey, hey
Did 'em in, did 'em in, did 'em in... ♪</i>

1664
01:27:20,985 --> 01:27:22,862
You have to say something to them.

1665
01:27:23,655 --> 01:27:26,324
<i>♪ Hit the switch
Imma shine the light up in the dark ♪</i>

1666
01:27:26,950 --> 01:27:29,285
Stop the music! Stop the music!

1667
01:27:29,369 --> 01:27:30,870
[music stops]

1668
01:27:31,788 --> 01:27:34,666
What in God's name is going on?
Pinky, please sit down.

1669
01:27:34,749 --> 01:27:38,920
Suneeta, Vijay, it is my duty to tell you
